 ('136', '186', 'en_us', 'Michele Stephens', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Michele', 'Stephens', 'Global Worship & Creative Arts Pastor', '<p>My name is Michele but I often answer to \"Shay\", \"Coach\", \"Mich\" and \"Mom\". These names come from relationships with my husband, co-workers, team members and my children.</p>\n\n<p>I have been married to my best friend, Chris (who happens to be the Sr. Pastor), for 25 years, and we have 3 awesome children Faith, Micah, and Zac as well as a brand new son-in-law, Frankie.</p>\n\n<p><strong>When I Met Jesus:</strong> I grew up in a godly home where my parents taught me how to study and memorize God?s word, share my faith, and most of all, worship. I began my relationship with Jesus at the age of 8 years old, and what a ride it has been!</p>\n\n<p><strong>My Calling:</strong> As far as a calling to be a worship leader ? that one kind of snuck up on me. I had grown up in a musical home where both of my parents lead in worship through singing and playing the guitar. My dad would make me play the piano and sing (at the time I hated it ? I was scared to death!) in church, during mission trips, or anywhere else he could find. After all those experiences, I guess I should have seen what was coming down the pike.</p>\n\n<p>I met my sweetheart at what was then called the BSU at UT-Chattanooga. He was going to be a preacher ? me a preacher?s wife?! But now I know that God had prepared me my whole life to be Chris? helpmate and ministry partner. I loved working in different areas as we began our ministry, but it seemed no matter what ministry it was, worship was at the heart.</p>\n\n<p>As the ministry assistant to the Worship Pastor at Faith Promise Church, they asked me to fill in when he left until they could find someone. Well, that was almost 9 years ago. God has confirmed to me over and over that He called me and put me where I am today ? I would have never believed it, and there is no way I could do what I do without the anointing and favor of the Lord.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Favorite Music:</strong> Anything Hillsong, anything Chris Tomlin, and ?clean? classic rock. (I am an ?80s girl.)</p>\n\n<p><strong>Hobbies:</strong> Anything with my family, scrapbooking, and photography.</p>', 'MicheleS@faithpromise.org', '1501', 'michele7317', 'michele7317', 'michele7317', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:19', '2017-09-01 18:24:07', 'c1439bcf-8121-445c-a72c-5f0d1257008d'),
 ('137', '187', 'en_us', 'Caroline Ervin', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Caroline', 'Ervin', 'Membership Director', '<p>Caroline Ervin has been on staff as the Membership Director since September 2006.</p>\n\n<p>She attended Samford University in Birmingham, Alabama, and graduated with a bachelors degree in Journalism and Mass Communication.  Caroline met her husband, Brad Ervin (who is also on staff at FPC), in college, and they were married in 2003.</p>\n\n<p>Caroline enjoys traveling and going on mission trips to China and Africa.  She also loves to read, shop, and spend time with her small group.</p>\n\n<p>Her biggest annoyance is when people ask her when she and Brad are going to start having kids.</p>', 'CarolineE@faithpromise.org', '1001', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:20', '2017-09-01 18:24:08', 'd9a072b6-fda4-4639-8027-a768e71e0ba2'),
 ('138', '188', 'en_us', 'Nancy Bachor', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Nancy', 'Bachor', 'Assistant to the Membership Director', '<p>My husband David and I started attending Faith Promise in October 2004. I came on staff in early 2007, and I am so humbled that God allows me to be even the tiniest part of what He is doing here at FPC!!</p>\n\n<p>In 1998 David, our two sons Sean and Ryan, and I set out from south Florida to our Promised Land, with hurricane Georges traveling along beside us.  Our little family of four that moved to East Tennessee has grown in the ten years that we have been here.  We have added to our family a lovely daughter-in-law, Christy, and two precious grandchildren, Colin and Audrey. We are blessed more than we could hope or imagine!!</p>\n\n<p>I love to spend time with my family, especially the grandkids, truly a gift from God!!  I have been classified by my husband as not just a book lover but a book collector.  I love to read - especially anything that draws me closer to the Lord. I also enjoy Sudoku, hiking, camping, geocaching, target practice, and riding the motorcycle with my hubby.</p>\n\n<p>My favorite food? It might be easier to list what I dont like... sushi, rhubarb, and liver.  Everything else is my favorite especially anything Italian, Mexican, Asian, Mediterranean, Cajun, or American.</p>\n\n<p>Unusual? Well, I would have to say yes, I am but thats not what you meant.  I want the truth, no matter how painful just give it to me straight, no fluff and please, please, do not beat around the bush!!! Oh yeah, and check out the left pinky toe when Im wearing flip-flops or barefoot.</p>\n\n<p>Facebook at Nancy Bachor</p>', 'NancyB@faithpromise.org', '1013', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:20', '2017-09-01 18:24:08', 'c1dabc12-9ca7-4604-8376-10cd7a30b637'),
 ('140', '190', 'en_us', 'Aaron Goin', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Aaron', 'Goin', 'Chief Financial Officer', '<p>Aaron Goin joined the staff of Faith Promise as Finance Director in August 2007, and in January 2011, Aaron took on the role of Chief Financial Officer. In this role he gets to work alongside great teams in Finance, Human Resources, Information Technology, Communications, Next Steps, and Facilities.</p>\n\n<p>Aaron and his wife Kerri were married in 2000. Their daughter Gracie was born in April 2006 and their son Mason was born in August of 2009. They love all things Disney, Dollywood, the beach, and any other kind of family adventure.</p>\n\n<p>In 2002, Aaron graduated from the University of Tennessee with a bachelor\'s degree in Finance. He received his Master of Business Administration degree in December 2010. Before joining the staff of Faith Promise, he worked for five years at Oak Ridge National Laboratory as a Subcontract Administrator.</p>\n\n<p>\"It has been an amazing journey to watch Faith Promise grow and to play a small part in that growth. Can\'t wait to see what God does as we continue to reach the world for Him.\"</p>', 'AaronG@faithpromise.org', '1602', NULL, 'aarongoin', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:22', '2017-09-01 18:24:12', 'd867e704-0706-4dbf-8fbf-044ab9c2f246'),
 ('141', '191', 'en_us', 'Robin Floyd', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Robin', 'Floyd', 'Assistant to the Financial Director', '<p>My family has attended Faith Promise, off and on, since they began meeting in the old church in Oak Ridge.  We served in other churches in between but kept returning to FPC and have been here since 2006.   I began working at Faith Promise in April 08.</p>\n\n<p>I love to read and spend time with my family.  I have 2 daughters. Chelsea is 14 and Lauren is 11, and their schedules take up most of my time outside work.  I have been married for 15 years to my husband, Greg.</p>\n\n<p>I homeschooled both of my children until last year.</p>\n\n<p>Any food is my favorite, except chicken livers, and I have a HUGE fear of heights.</p>', 'rfloyd@faithpromise.org', '1600', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '2017-09-01 18:24:13', 'ac14a287-2146-4d15-9b30-04848d51c65b'),
 ('142', '192', 'en_us', 'Chris Cox', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Chris', 'Cox', 'Facilities Director', '<p>Amy and I started attending Faith Promise in 2004. We were married January 2005, and we have two children, Lexie and Brayden. I\'ve been on staff since January 2007.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Random Facts:</strong> I grew up in Oliver Springs, TN, and I was a junior olympic in white water kayaking.  I like to fish, play golf, and spend time with my family.  I will eat just about any kind of food, but my favorite is lasagna. My wife can whip me at Guitar Hero. Some people may not know this, but I almost pass out whenever I see blood.</p>', 'ChrisC@faithpromise.org', '1703', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '2017-09-01 18:24:13', '37ce6266-75d4-45b3-bea1-73b40c54fc75'),
 ('143', '193', 'en_us', 'Adrianne Adams', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Adrianne', 'Adams', 'Housekeeper', NULL, 'AdrianneA@faithpromise.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '2017-09-01 18:24:13', 'f94ed43e-81e6-414b-a8b1-053fb5be3f7a'),
 ('144', '194', 'en_us', 'Adam McCue', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Adam', 'McCue', 'Worship Associate', '<p>Hey everyone Im Adam!</p>\n\n<p>I have been part of Faith Promise Church since early 2000. Started volunteering Day 1 (somewhat under my own volition). Serving is BIG here, and its a blast!</p>\n\n<p>I volunteered in Worship for a long time.  That\'s where I learned to play some music enough to make me dangerous, anyway.  After seven years or so, when they realized I wouldnt leave, I was brought on staff. Somewhere in there (2006), I graduated from UTK with a Finance/Economics degree, which I use everyday.  Hahaha.</p>\n\n<p>Hobbies? Uhhhhh I like to play golf, soccer, and most other sports. I love to snow ski! I enjoy going to restaurants with my fianc, Mary Beth Rader, and hanging out with her in general.</p>\n\n<p>Unusual? well, I was a competitive power tumbler during the high school years. We went all over the south-east to meets and competitions and stuff super fun!</p>\n\n<p>Hit me up on Facebook, or find me after a service and introduce yourself, I LOVE that!!!</p>', 'AdamM@faithpromise.org', '1505', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:24', '2017-09-01 18:24:13', 'aa086209-535a-4d6b-a7b3-52fb3b6e12a5'),
 ('145', '195', 'en_us', 'Mia Hannahs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Mia', 'Hannahs', 'Blount Campus fpKids Director', '<p>Mia joined the FPC staff in August of 2005, after meeting Pastor Chris at Ripleys Believe It or Not in Gatlinburg. She has a passion for early childhood education and has been working with preschoolers and their families for twenty years.</p>\n\n<p>She grew up in a big family that enjoyed music and art and is the last of seven kids. Now, she is the mother to Parker [an aspiring artist], Tyler [a self-proclaimed sci-fi fanatic] and Kylie [who loves horseback riding].</p>\n\n<p>She enjoys singing, reading, camping, and creating. Her greatest hope-  helping multitudes of families and volunteers develop a strong spiritual foundation in young children. Her greatest fear- being trapped in a car underwater.</p>', 'MiaH@faithpromise.org', '1200', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:24', '2017-09-01 18:24:14', 'c3b30734-1f35-43c4-8868-955bf9be048d'),
 ('146', '196', 'en_us', 'Pam Bakker', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Pam', 'Bakker', 'Assistant to the PromiseKids Director', '<p>Pam has been at Faith Promise since June 2001 and came on staff December 2007.  Her favorite hobbies include cooking and reading.</p>\n\n<p>Her favorite food is Mexican or pasta, least favorite is veggies, and greatest fear is not making a difference for Jesus.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Something unusual about yourself?</strong><br /> I grew up inn Southern California, and I am the mother of twins, born by surrogacy (my sister).</p>\n\n<p><strong>If you could be any animal, what would it be?</strong><br />A bird.  I\'d love to travel around and see everything!</p>', 'PamB@faithpromise.org', '1201', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:24', '2017-09-01 18:24:14', '66abfb3e-426f-49f0-b8fa-e6670beee0a3'),
 ('147', '197', 'en_us', 'Jennifer Loveday', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Jennifer', 'Loveday', 'KidK\'nex Programming Director', '<p>Among her other attributes, Jennifer is a fan of people (all shapes, sizes, ages, and backgrounds).  After five years on staff at Faith Promise, she currently works with people of the smaller variety in our K-5th grade Childrens Ministry (KidKnex) program.  Originally from Knoxville, Jennifer returned home after several treks in professional theaters, tours, and ministries.  She holds a degree in Communication and Theater Arts from the University of the Cumberlands.  As KidKnex Programming Director, she incorporates her love for Christ, children and creative storytelling each weekend into a Large Group teaching environment.  She enjoys smiles,  laughter, energy, fun, insight, and sincerity from all our wonderful Faith Promise kids.</p>', 'JenniferL@faithpromise.org', '1102', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:24', '2017-09-01 18:24:14', 'c408aa10-e60f-4ba6-bc6d-8f54f7de636e'),
 ('148', '198', 'en_us', 'Susan Troop', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Susan', 'Troop', 'Kids Hope Coordinator ', '<p>Susan Troop has been on staff part time since October of 2006.  She served as the Mothers Day Out Director prior to taking the position of Kids Hope USA Director.</p>\n\n<p>She attended the University of Vermont, where she earned her bachelors degree in Elementary Education.  She has ten years of teaching experience.</p>\n\n<p>Susan met her husband and was married in Orlando, FL in 1993.  While growing up in Vermont, she has also lived in Florida, Kansas, and Virginia before settling in Knoxville.</p>\n\n<p>Susan is the mother of three girls and two dogs.  She enjoys shopping, naps, and special times with the family.  She also enjoys going on mission trips and has especially loved traveling to South Africa.</p>', 'SusanT@faithpromise.org', '1202', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:25', '2017-09-01 18:24:15', 'c719171d-e150-457d-be0c-03c9c4868019'),
 ('149', '199', 'en_us', 'Caitie Maylott', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Caitie', 'Maylott', 'Caitie Maylott', NULL, 'CaitieM@faithpromise.org', '1203', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:25', '2017-09-01 18:24:15', 'e79809ae-ae6f-49b4-9275-089268a7ac93'),
 ('150', '200', 'en_us', 'Cheryl Christensen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Cheryl', 'Christensen', 'Administrative Support Assistant', '<p>Cheryl and her family have been at Faith Promise since 2003, and she came on staff in January 2008.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Favorite Hobbies:</strong><br /> I like to travel, hang out with my boyfriend of 25 years, go to the movies, and do girl things with my daughters!</p>\n\n<p><strong>Something Unusual:</strong><br /> My husband was in the Navy for 20 years, and I was the command liaison for the submarine, USS Tennessee, for 4 years.</p>\n\n<p><strong>If you could be any animal, what would it be?</strong><br /> I would be a dog! They give unconditional love, and they get to eat, sleep, and play all day.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Life Calling:</strong><br /> I love missions, and Greg and I intend to go into full time missions one day. Every trip I\'ve ever been on has been great! I have been to Thailand 2 times, Macau, and Capetown.</p>', 'CherylC@faithpromise.org', '1000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:25', '2017-09-01 18:24:16', 'b80d556c-425e-4afe-b7b7-2ec775de4b00'),
 ('151', '201', 'en_us', 'Teresa Merritt', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Teresa', 'Merritt', 'Assistant to the High School Pastor', '<p>Teresa is a Knoxville native with a BS degree from UT. She has three grown children (a son and two married daughters). She and her husband, Mark, have been members at Faith Promise Church since 2005. Teresa is passionate about young people finding their God-designed purpose in life and living the abundant life that Jesus promises those who seek Him with their whole heart.</p>\n\n<p><strong>HOBBY:</strong> READING</p>\n\n<p><strong>UNUSUAL:</strong> I love microbiology &amp; biochemistry</p>\n\n<p><strong>ANIMAL:</strong> A fat, lazy cat (one that could read, preferably)</p>\n\n<p><strong>FAVORITE FOOD:</strong> Vanilla ice cream (not because its boring but because of all the ways it can be changed!)</p>', 'TeresaM@faithpromise.org', '1300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:26', '2017-09-01 18:24:16', '9fc4abd2-6d99-4e02-809d-fa05699a19e8'),
 ('153', '203', 'en_us', 'Matt Grimes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Matt', 'Grimes', 'Blount Campus Pastor', '<p>Matt grew up in Alabama and went to college at Samford University in Birmingham, where he graduated with a degree in religious studies. He also holds a Master\'s degree in Christian Education from New Orleans Seminary. Matt has served in student ministry at Faith Promise Church since 2005 where he established and built the middle school ministry before taking over all students in 2013.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to his work at Faith Promise and his time traveling and speaking at conferences and events, Matt also serves on staff with Ken Davis and Michael Hyatt as a Communication Coach for Dynamic Communicators International.</p>\n\n<p>Matt is married to Carmen, and they have a beautiful daughter, Elin who was born in 2011.</p>', 'MattG@faithpromise.org', '1706', 'matt.grimes.7', 'mattgrimes', 'themattgrimes', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:28', '2017-09-01 18:24:20', '6277f1f1-4f32-42df-8fc3-1090b88df8fc'),
 ('155', '205', 'en_us', 'Brad Ervin', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Brad', 'Ervin', 'Pastor of Outreach and Missions', '<p>Brad Ervin is the Pastor of Outreach and Missions at Faith Promise. He joined the staff in Nov 2007, and he and his wife Caroline have been attending faith promise since February of 2006. Brad is a huge Vol fan and loves sports in general. He graduated with a BS in Business Marketing from Samford University in 2001.</p>\n\n<p>Hobbies include: reading (Tolkien/Ayn Rand/Robert Jordan some favs), travel, music (especially British Rock), movies, broadway and west end musicals, and sucking the marrow out of life. He is also an accomplished break dancer and pole vaulter.</p>\n\n<p>Facebook him Brad Ervin, twitter: BradErvin and myspace: Volcrazy.</p>', 'BradE@faithpromise.org', '1405', 'bradervin', 'bradervin', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:30', '2017-09-01 18:24:21', '7e9a70e6-1133-4464-88a2-c29edc03b588'),
 ('157', '207', 'en_us', 'Jaclyn Holloway', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Jaclyn', 'Holloway', 'fpCreative Project Manager', '<p>A beach girl at heart that fell in love with the mountains, Jaclyn moved to Knoxville from Virginia Beach in 2005. Jaclyn has a B.S. in Communications from the University of Tennessee with a focus on video production. She has been a part of the worship ministry staff since 2011 and feels extremely blessed to be part of such a talented and creative team. She enjoys film producing and acting as part of her ministry, especially when humor is involved.</p>\n\n<p>When she goes home, she gets to play her favorite role: a wife and mother. Her husband, Phil Holloway is also on staff in the worship ministry as the Vocal Director. They are blessed with two very active boys, Jameson and Jude. Favorite family hobbies include dance parties with Yo Gabba Gabba, drag racing hot wheels, and extreme water balloon fights. Follow their adventures on twitter: @HollowayJaclyn, snapchat: jhollaback, Instagram: jholloway1120</p>', 'JaclynH@faithpromise.org', '1503', NULL, 'HollowayJaclyn', 'jholloway1120', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '2017-09-01 18:24:25', '234533b0-0135-4b3f-9219-2170184e1a4d'),
 ('158', '208', 'en_us', 'Debbie McChesney', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Debbie', 'McChesney', 'Worship Assistant', '<p>On November 18th, 1999, during her freshman year of college at the University of the Cumberlands, Debbie surrendered her heart and life to Christ. In 2004, she married the love of her life, Adam, and they began attending Faith Promise in 2005.</p>\n\n<p>Both Debbie and Adam serve in the worship ministry, and Debbie joined the worship staff in November of 2007. She is the proud mother of a beautiful little girl, Abigail, and enjoys karaoke, scrapbooking, and spending time with her family.</p>', 'DebbieM@faithpromise.org', '1503', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '2017-09-01 18:24:26', 'e695eb47-cffa-4f62-9061-ca0bee851093'),
 ('159', '209', 'en_us', 'Nolan Smith', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Nolan', 'Smith', 'Worship Technical Director', NULL, 'nolan@faithpromise.org', '1504', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '2017-09-01 18:24:26', 'd98d46dc-aef8-433b-861a-b265708d89d4'),
 ('161', '211', 'en_us', 'Kyle Gilbert', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Kyle', 'Gilbert', 'Pastor of Communications & Internet Campus Pastor', '<p>Kyle came on staff at Faith Promise Church in October 2008 as the Pastor of Communications. He oversees web technology, graphic design, the Internet Campus, and helping get the word out about our church.</p>\n\n<p>He and his wife, Keri, were married in 1999 and haven\'t owned a TV since then. They have four crazy-awesome kids, including a set of twins.</p>\n\n<p>Kyle has gone skydiving, and he once went scuba diving in the Black Sea after five minutes of instruction (in Russian).</p>\n\n<p>For fun, Kyle loves to play disc golf and racquetball, and he plays both poorly but with enthusiasm.</p>\n\n<p>You can keep up with Kyle on his blog at <a href=\"http://kylesrandom.com\">KylesRandom.com</a> or <a href=\"http://twitter.com/kylegilbert\">follow him on Twitter</a>.</p>', 'KyleG@faithpromise.org', '1704', 'kylegilbert', 'kylegilbert', 'kylegilbert', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:36', '2017-09-01 18:24:30', '6b7c9cfe-1ffd-4e7f-bced-a43540fde33c'),
 ('163', '213', 'en_us', 'Sid Spiva', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Sid', 'Spiva', 'Multisite Facilities Director', '<p>Sid is a lifelong resident of Clinton and Anderson County. After working in Anderson County Schools for 32 years as a High School Teacher and Principal, Sid entered full time ministry in 2008. He joined the Faith Promise staff when the Anderson County Campus opened in 2013.</p>\n\n<p>Sid and his wife Judy of 40 years have two outstanding sons, two wonderful daughter-in-laws, and two awesome grandsons.</p>\n\n<p>He enjoys traveling, riding motorcycles, music, and spending time with family.</p>', 'SidS@faithpromise.org', NULL, 'sid.spiva', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:38', '2017-09-01 18:24:34', 'df9722f7-3e53-40ce-87ae-47eed27a9e83'),
 ('165', '215', 'en_us', 'Emily Carringer', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Emily', 'Carringer', 'Production Pastor', '<p>My husband, Chuck, and I have been at Faith Promise Church since the very first service at the Garden Plaza Hotel in Oak Ridge. However, I didn\'t join the FPC staff until 2003.</p>\n\n<p>It has been an adventure ever since. You really never know what each day will hold. We have two great kids that have grown up at FPC. Zach is 14 and Maggie is 11. When we\'re not at church, we love eating out and hanging out together as a family.</p>\n\n<p>I love to read, have fun, and laugh a lot, usually at myself. One of the coolest parts about what I get to do is to help others be a part of the Worship Ministry and serve where they are passionate.</p>', 'EmilyC@faithpromise.org', '1500', 'emily.carringer', 'emilycarringer', 'emilycarringer', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:41', '2017-09-01 18:24:35', '3a97329c-18dd-4355-8617-e58dc77fa1a0'),
 ('167', '217', 'en_us', 'Jennifer Patrick', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Jennifer', 'Patrick', 'Group Assimilation Coordinator', '<p>Jennifer has been attending Faith Promise Church since January 2002. Soon afterwards, she and her family attended a small group, and that began her love for small group ministry. She started out as a volunteer in small group ministry, and she\'s been on staff since 2005.</p>\n\n<p>In her free time, she and her husband, Rob love to spend time at the lake with friends and family and make frequent visits to the Smoky mountains.</p>', 'JenniferP@faithpromise.org', '1403', 'jennifer.c.patrick.94', NULL, 'jenniferlpatrick', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:44', '2017-09-01 18:24:35', 'af55fa6a-712a-42da-b139-9358c22eb401'),
 ('169', '219', 'en_us', 'Heather Burson', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Heather', 'Burson', 'Graphic Designer', '<p>Hi, I\'m Heather. I\'m a native East Tennessean, graduate of the University of Tennessee, and a die-hard Vols fan. My husband, Mike, and I enjoy travel, college football, and a little friendly competition now and again.</p>\n\n<p>On staff since 2007, I love being a member of the Communications Team (part of the Admin staff) and a keeper of the Faith Promise brand. One of my favorite things about designing at Faith Promise is the variety of projects that come my way, but by far the best thing is that is I get to be part of an awesome team that is impacting the world for Christ.</p>', 'HeatherB@faithpromise.org', '1014', 'heatherburson', 'heatherburson', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:47', '2017-09-01 18:25:06', 'a2563b70-fdb7-4271-a003-4ee4cb2ef19c'),
 ('171', '221', 'en_us', 'Drew Wells', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Drew', 'Wells', 'Pastor of Discipleship', '<p>Drew began attending Faith Promise in 1995. In 2001, he started as an intern for the Student Ministry and eventually came on full-time in 2003 as the Student Ministry Program Director, the Pastor of Young Adults in 2007, and after some brief training on the swamp planet of Dagobah, returned to staff in 2017 as the Pastor of Discipleship.</p>\n\n<p>Drew married his beautiful bride Sandy in 2005 and is the proud father of two sons, Justus and Theo. Before becoming a family man, he graduated college from Pellissippi State Community College with an AS in General Sciences in 2003 and from Tusculum College with BS in Organizational Management in 2006.</p>\n\n<p>Aside from being an avid reader, aspiring writer, and closet cinephile, he also enjoys using his vacation days to sit front row at Nissan or Wrigley Field to watch his beloved Titans and Cubs.</p>', 'DrewW@faithpromise.org', '1302', NULL, 'dreWells', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:50', '2017-09-01 18:25:09', '48ae9826-d619-4c5f-bc3e-69df780bc7c4'),
 ('172', '222', 'en_us', 'Evan Crass', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Evan', 'Crass', 'Associate Pastor of Groups', '<p>Evan serves as a pastor in the groups office at Faith Promise Church. Although Evan rolled on staff in July 2008, he has been a part of FPC since the very beginning. Prior to becoming a staff member, he served in various areas, including the Leadership Team and the Management Team and has continuously served as a group leader since returning home for graduate school in 1998.</p>\n\n<p>Evans background includes working with start-ups and emerging companies, and he continues to consult with these companies, specifically in the areas of operations and finance. It is this same passion to see new companies grow that drives him to create and nurture new and creative groups to connect people with God and others.  These groups form the foundation for the churchs diverse offering of interest groups.</p>\n\n<p>He and his wife, Marta, were married in May 2000. They have a daughter, Kate, who was added to the family in May 2007, and a son, Andrew, who was born in December 2009. The extended family includes the hundreds of people who have been a part of their group over the years.</p>\n\n<p>You can connect with Evan on <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/evancrass\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Facebook</a> or on <a href=\"http://twitter.com/evancrass\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Twitter</a>.</p>', 'EvanC@faithpromise.org', '1404', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:50', '2017-09-01 18:25:09', '0d8f234c-7d13-48c2-b9f4-a5de9a3866d9'),
 ('173', '223', 'en_us', 'Phil Bledsoe', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Phil', 'Bledsoe', 'Technical Director', '<p><strong>About Me:</strong> I was born in Tallahassee, Florida, and was raised in Georgia - mostly around the Atlanta area. My family was a very strong Christian family and all of us were involved in the church from an early age.</p>\n\n<p>I moved to Nashville in 1998 to pursue a degree in Music Business and Recording. I was in a band but transitioned to the production side of things when I moved to Nashville. Originally, I was focused on a future in studio work, but God continually gave me more opportunities in live production.  I began working for artists with whom I had played in my performing days and those jobs quickly opened more opportunities deeper into the Christian Music Industry. I spent a few years in audio, a few years in lighting and transitioned back to Audio with the added responsibility of tour managing for bands such as Skillet and Tree63. For the past 7 years I\'ve taken off in the fall to production manage a 15-20 band traveling music festival called SHOUTfest, showcasing many major industry headliners such as Third Day and Newsboys.</p>\n\n<p>I was married in 2002 to my beautiful bride, Shanell. She is originally from the Knoxville area but we met at MTSU in 2000. We travelled together for years until she launched a successful photography business in 2007. My decision to leave the glamour of the road is based around our great desire to start a family. We\'ve been blessed with the opportunity to join the FP family and are looking forward to growing our family internally and externally!</p>\n\n<p><strong>Interesting Fact:</strong> Shanell and I took a two-month honeymoon and travelled the entire US and Canada (including Hawaii).</p>', 'PhilB@faithpromise.org', '1510', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:50', '2017-09-01 18:25:10', '46620806-a227-4928-b84a-9e591e77990c'),
 ('174', '224', 'en_us', 'Krista McBroom', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Krista', 'McBroom', 'Receptionist', '<p>Krista has attended Faith Promise since May 2007.  She first came on staff as a summer intern for the student ministry and has been on staff since January 2008.</p>\n\n<p>She attended Carson Newman College where she got her degree in Child and Family Studies.  She has also started working on her Masters in Christian Education.</p>\n\n<p>She likes to read, scrapbook, and be outside.  But her favorite thing to do is writing poetry and devotionals.</p>\n\n<p>Something unusual about her is that she is left handed.</p>', 'krista@faithpromise.org', '1000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '2017-09-01 18:25:10', 'd1c56309-d8b3-4fe2-beae-e3ee009b3c38'),
 ('175', '225', 'en_us', 'Justin Truluck', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Justin', 'Truluck', 'Live Production Director', '<p>Born in Farragut, I was raised as a second generation Christian and was brought up in and around the church in all elements of life. At the age of 13, with no understanding of how things worked, I was put behind a sound board to fill a need for the church I was serving in and have never looked back.</p>\n\n<p>In 2004 I graduated from Farragut High school and joined the staff at M&amp;L Sound where my passion and understanding for all things audio continued to grow.</p>\n\n<p>During my final years in grade school, I decided that I needed to experience the world in a new and truly unique way, so I opted to study abroad and continue developing my understanding of God and his plan. I did this by attending Southern Cross College in Sydney Australia where I graduated in 2008 with a Bachelors of Theology in Christian Ministry. During that time I continued to serve God through my involvement in a church production department and had the opportunity to be involved in many large-scale events which continued to build my understanding of all aspects of Production.</p>\n\n<p>Today I am continuing to grow personally and corporately and I can\'t wait to see what God has in store for the future.</p>', 'JustinT@faithpromise.org', '1515', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '2017-09-01 18:25:10', '27753ef8-44ed-4222-832d-242568a09c01'),
 ('176', '226', 'en_us', 'Tanya Tumminello', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Tanya', 'Tumminello', 'KidKnex Ministry Assistant', NULL, 'TanyaT@faithpromise.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '2017-09-01 18:25:10', '1b2e47bd-340d-422c-a94f-a058cce4d4b1'),
 ('177', '227', 'en_us', 'Matt James', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Matt', 'James', 'Video Director', '<p>I am a Geek. Now, a lot of people associate geekdom with those guys in High School who had absolutely zero people skills. Those are nerds. Geeks are the hybrids who get along and enjoy the company of people as well as the company of technology. Therefore, I am a Geek.</p>\n\n<p>I\'m overly educated with a BS degree in Television Production from MTSU (Go Chicken Horses! err... Raiders!) as well as surviving a five-year apprenticeship in the IBEW. So, I\'m either an Electrician who dabbles in Video Production or a Video Producer who dabbles in Electrical work.</p>\n\n<p>Hobbies include reading, home improvement, four wheeling in my Jeep, Movies, Music, as well as a select few TV shows. Reading is usually something Science Fiction flavored. I\'ve also branched spiritual growth books since I became a Christian. Favorite books include Dune, Blue like Jazz, and Velvet Elvis. I also have a weakness for Stephen Kings writing.</p>\n\n<p>My taste in movies is all over the map - from classics such as Metropolis to more modern works like Coraline. Musical tastes are also all over the map... From Rock, to Classical, to Bluegrass - I\'ll listen to anything. TV shows such as Lost, Eli Stone, NCIS, Good Eats, and Battlestar Galactica (the new one) are among those set to record on my DVR.</p>\n\n<p>I\'ve been a member of Faith Promise since 2002 when I accepted Jesus as my Lord and Savior. Shortly after that, I started volunteering in the Video Ministry. Since then, I\'ve I joined the staff as Video Director. In what I hope is an indicator of things to come, my first three days on staff were snow days.</p>\n\n<p>If you want, look me up on Facebook or just send me an email. I\'m always up for email, something about being a geek....</p>\n\n<p>Or, check out my blog: <a href=\"http://realtater.blogspot.com\">realtater.blogspot.com</a>.</p>', 'MattJ@faithpromise.org', '1520', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:52', '2017-09-01 18:25:11', '39f85a9b-a051-4f74-ae87-e9f590d68693'),
 ('178', '228', 'en_us', 'Roger Owens', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Roger', 'Owens', 'Campbell Campus Groups Pastor & Missions Coordinator', NULL, 'RogerO@faithpromise.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:52', '2017-09-01 18:25:11', 'bed9aac2-7592-4a37-8adb-71aab322fa3b'),
 ('180', '230', 'en_us', 'Zac Stephens', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Zac', 'Stephens', 'Farragut Campus Pastor', '', 'ZacS@faithpromise.org', '1304', 'zac.stephens.71', 'fps_pastorzac', 'fps_pastorzac', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:54', '2017-09-01 18:25:15', 'ad08e187-c615-48f8-ad44-fe9d05929be6'),
 ('182', '232', 'en_us', 'Dr. Chuck Carringer', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Chuck', 'Carringer', 'Pastor of Leadership Development & Stewardship', '<p>In my role as Pastor of Leadership Development and Stewardship I partner with staff and volunteers to increase leadership capacity and stewardship across Faith Promise. From 2009-2014 I served as Pastor of Family Ministry. Prior to joining the staff I served for 24 years in public schools. From 1990-2009 I was part of the faculty at Oak Ridge High School serving in a variety of roles including: teacher, coach, vice principal, athletic director, and principal.</p>\n\n<p>My wife Emily, of 25 years, and I have been members of Faith Promise since the church began. I volunteered in a number of ministry areas including serving as an elder, student ministry, school of leaders, and membership classes.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to my role at Faith Promise I provide executive coaching to business leaders. I have a doctorate in executive leadership as well as being a John Maxwell Team Certified Coach, Speaker and Trainer. In addition to executive coaching, I speak frequently to business teams and organizations.</p>\n\n<p>I enjoy family time, and Em, Zach (20 years old), and Maggie (17 years old). We love traveling, especially to the beach! In addition to family fun I enjoy sports, reading, exercising, and time with friends.</p>\n\n<p>Follow Chuck on <a href=\"http://twitter.com/chuckcarringer\">Twitter</a>, <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/chuckcarringer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Facebook</a>, or <a href=\"http://www.chuckcarringer.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">his blog</a>.</p>', 'ChuckC@faithpromise.org', '1101', 'chuckcarringer', 'chuckcarringer', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:57', '2017-09-01 18:25:19', '4e607733-d953-4f6e-abb0-83c16cf4143e'),
 ('183', '233', 'en_us', 'Melanie Goodman', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Melanie', 'Goodman', 'Assistant to the Middle School Pastor', '<p>We started attending Faith Promise Church in 2007, and I joined the awesome Faith Promise Family Ministry Staff in February 2009.  I am very blessed to be given the opportunity to serve God doing the very thing God has equipped me for!  I am the assistant to the Middle School Pastor and love working with the student ministry staff and students.  I have an overwhelming desire to help teenage students experience a personal relationship with God and help equip them with the tools they need to make good choices that will impact their lives forever.</p>\n\n<p>I\'ve been happily married to my husband Jonathan Goodman since January 18, 1992.  I\'m the luckiest lady alive to be married to the love of my life and best friend!!  Along with Jonathan came a special blessing, my step-son Justin who I love very much.  Together Jonathan and I have two children, Zeke and Darah.  We love spending time together as a family.  We camp, ride bikes, run, and love anything that involves a beach.  We have fun doing anything as long as were together.</p>\n\n<p>I was extremely blessed for the privilege and support of my husband to be able to stay home to raise my children for 15 years.  During that time I worked part time as a children\'s ministry director at a previous church and also as a substitute teacher.  I spent numerous hours volunteering and loving every minute I spent being with Zeke and Darah.  I am humbled that God would loan such precious children to me so I could be their mom!</p>\n\n<p>Hobbies:  I love to read anything that helps me to grow spiritually, and my guilty pleasure: Karen Kingsbury novels.  I love to run!  Yes I said it, I love to run!  When I\'ve had a stressful day, running always sets me at ease.  I use this time to meditate on all God has for me - except for the times I\'m begging God to get me through the next mile!</p>\n\n<p>Favorite bible verse: Search me, O God, and know my heart; test me and know my anxious thoughts.  See if there is any offensive way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.  Psalm 139: 23-24</p>', 'MelanieG@faithpromise.org', '1305', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:57', '2017-09-01 18:25:20', '53c8dfda-6aab-453e-8027-474670f6e4d5'),
 ('184', '234', 'en_us', 'Deneen Lambert', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Deneen', 'Lambert', 'Finance Assistant', NULL, 'DeneenL@faithpromise.org', '1600', 'deneen.lambert', 'deneenl14', 'deneenl', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:41:58', '2017-09-01 18:25:20', 'd16c55c8-ab25-4ab6-bb2d-2f7490f0ffe8'),
 ('186', '236', 'en_us', 'Joe Filipowicz', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Joe', 'Filipowicz', 'IT Director', '<p>I was born in Toledo Ohio but moved to Knoxville in 1989.  While I like Tennessee Football I am a die hard Ohio State fan!</p>\n\n<p>My wife Donna and I started dating in high school and have been married for {{ \'1994-10-01\' | age }} awesome years. We have two kids  Katie, {{ \'1995-10-01\' | age }} and Brandon, {{ \'1998-09-01\' | age }}.  Katie is a sophomore at the University of Tennessee and Brandon is a Junior in high school. They are both involved with the church and we couldnt be prouder of who they have become!!</p>\n\n<p>I have been working at Faith Promise Church for {{ \'2009-09-01\' | age }} years and love coming to work everyday!  I enjoy Basketball, soccer, football and... well pretty much anything thats competitive.</p>', 'JoeF@faithpromise.org', '1605', 'joe.filipowicz.jr', 'joeflip2', 'joeflip', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:00', '2017-09-01 18:25:25', 'ef0486ee-1e94-4e61-a4e2-fb3bd8ddab27'),
 ('187', '237', 'en_us', 'Rachel Christensen', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Rachel', 'Christensen', 'Worship Resources', '<p>Hi! Im Rachel. I became a part of Faith Promise in 2003 after my family moved here from Charleston, South Carolina. Ive always had a passion for music - but I cant think of anything better than using it (along with other creative elements) as a tool to glorify the incredible God we serve. So I started getting in the middle of dramas and worship through the youth group. I kept coming around and ended up interning for several years with the worship ministry.</p>\n\n<p>I officially became a part of the staff the summer of 2009. My official title is Worship Resources, which means I oversee fpResources along with other odd jobs to help the Worship Ministry function each week. Im super excited about what God is doing here and cant wait to see how Hes going to use me to further His kingdom!</p>\n\n<p>Im currently working on my Bachelors Degree in English (and I feel like Ill never finish!) and I LOVE studying abroad. I have a passion for missions and music, and I have no idea what God wants to do with it, but Im totally willing to take the path He leads me down. For fun I like to read (I know Im a nerd!), play Rock Band (the best game of all time) and I really enjoy quality time of any sort with friends (especially if Starbucks is involved).</p>', 'RachelC@faithpromise.org', '1525', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '2017-09-01 18:25:25', '2260e6f8-c592-40b7-9b21-f4e7ddb43799'),
 ('188', '238', 'en_us', 'Natali South', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Natali', 'South', 'Assistant to the Pastor of Family Ministries', NULL, 'NataliS@faithpromise.org', '1100', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '2017-09-01 18:25:25', 'eaf8d251-6880-4447-bd17-094c336307ff'),
 ('189', '239', 'en_us', 'Michael Wallace', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Michael', 'Wallace', 'High School Pastor', '<p>Michael grew up in Greensboro, North Carolina, and graduated from Appalachian State University. Upon graduation, he married his wife, Holly, and they moved to Texas. While in Dallas, Michael earned a Masters in Christian Education from Dallas Theological Seminary and spent five years working with both middle and high school students.</p>\n\n<p>In December of 2009, Michael, Holly and their 2 year old son, Colt, migrated back east to join the Faith Promise staff. Michael and Holly love to spend time hanging out as a family and are eagerly awaiting the birth of their second child this spring!</p>\n\n<p>While Michael loves all sports, he has a special place in his heart for UNC basketball, Virginia Tech football and the Dallas Cowboys. (He is working desperately to become a Vols fan as well!) In addition to enjoying sports, Michael can usually be found listening to good music or watching a great movie.</p>\n\n<p>As a side note, if you want to be in his eternal good favor, all it takes is a cold can of Cheerwine. Just in case you were wondering....</p>\n\n<p>You can connect with him via <a title=\"http://www.facebook.com/michaelbwallace\" href=\"http://www.facebook.com/michaelbwallace\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Facebook</a>, <a title=\"http://www.twitter.com/michaelbwallace\" href=\"http://www.twitter.com/michaelbwallace\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Twitter</a>, or <a title=\"http://www.michaelbwallace.com\" href=\"http://www.michaelbwallace.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">his blog</a>.</p>', 'MichaelW@faithpromise.org', '1301', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '2017-09-01 18:25:26', 'd7aef57e-cee9-491e-b28f-e865f4babcc7'),
 ('190', '240', 'en_us', 'Jason Stubbs', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Jason', 'Stubbs', 'Worship Associate - Vocal Director', '<p>Jason is originally from the beautiful archipelagic country of the Bahamas, where he was born and raised until coming to the US to attend college. Jason is from a strong Christian family that valued faith, education and community service as essential to living out Gods purpose. In this vein Jason has completed undergraduate studies in Psychology/Theology/ Music and further graduate seminary studies in Church Ministry/Counseling. He is currently pursuing is doctoral studies in leadership and ministry. Jason believes that God has called all believers to live life to its fullest. Jason enjoys worship and is passionate about seeing people connect with God through worship and the Word.</p>\n\n<p>Jason has had ministry experience serving as an assistant vocal director for a major Christian university traveling singing group and worship ministry intern and worship pastor in several ministry settings. While in university Jason met his stunning, godly wife and is eternally grateful for the resplendent beauty that she illuminates not only externally but internally.</p>\n\n<p>Jason enjoys running, go-carts, cricket (a Caribbean sport) and baseball.  Jason is also a social activist and believes that believers also share social responsibility as essential to expressing our Christian care and concern.</p>\n\n<p>Jason has been attending Faith Promise since fall of 2006 and engaged actively in the worship ministry since fall 2007. Jason is a Worship Associate and works with the vocals, and he wants you to be a part of the ministry. He wants you to come ready to have fun while we create, connect and assist in bringing about life change in the lives of people.</p>\n\n<p>Favorite scripture:</p>\n\n<p>\"For by grace you have been saved through faith; and that not of yourselves, it is the gift of God; not as a result of works, that no one should boast.\" Eph. 2:8-9</p>', 'JasonS@faithpromise.org', '1530', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '2017-09-01 18:25:26', '49ef7ea8-7c70-4e63-9355-58c047737765'),
 ('192', '242', 'en_us', 'Gina McClain', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Gina', 'McClain', 'Pastor of Children\'s Ministries', '<p>Gina is originally from Broken Arrow, Oklahoma. A graduate of the University of Central Oklahoma, she worked in International Banking before God interrupted her career goals. Gina began working for LifeChurch.tv in 1999. Compelled to work with kids and families, Gina found her rhythm in leveraging what happens at church to impact what happens at home.</p>\n\n<p>Gina is driven by the idea of equipping parents for the journey of teaching their kids how to follow Christ. Based upon her experience as a mom, she identifies with the everyday challenges parents wade through. Most of which seem more messy than spiritual. And yet, in the midst of the mess we have the opportunity to demonstrate Jesus to our kids. It\'s the most difficult, challenging &amp; rewarding thing we will ever do.</p>\n\n<p>Gina and Kyle were married in 1994 and have three kids, Keegan Josie &amp; Connor. Following the call to join the Faith Promise family, Kyle and Gina packed up their family in February 2010 and moved to Knoxville.</p>\n\n<p>Gina is a writer, a speaker, a mentor and a coffee snob. If you\'re looking to grease her palm, a double-shot Americano will do the trick.</p>\n\n<p>You can read more about Gina on <a href=\"http://www.ginamcclain.com/\">her blog</a>, follow her on <a href=\"http://twitter.com/gina_mcclain\">Twitter</a>, or \"friend\"  on <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/gina.mcclain\">Facebook</a>.</p>', 'GinaM@faithpromise.org', '1204', 'gina.mcclain', 'gina_mcclain', 'ginamcclain', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:04', '2017-09-01 18:25:31', '1abed8aa-2c9c-4006-92df-c207a5225861'),
 ('193', '243', 'en_us', 'Paul McNeill', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Paul', 'McNeill', 'Student Ministry Program Director', '<p>Paul was born in New York but moved shortly thereafter and was raised in Knoxville, Tennessee.  Paul grew up as a middle child, and accredits middle child syndrome as the cause of his outgoing personality and constant humor.</p>\n\n<p>Paul began his call to ministry during high school, working many summers at a Christian camp in Asheville, North Carolina.  He later attended Boyce College at Southern Seminary in Louisville, Kentucky, studying Youth Ministry and Biblical studies, and then returned to Tennessee in 2007 to pursue a degree in Video Production at Pellissippi State.  A year and a half later, he met his beautiful wife Kelly, and the 2 were married in May 2010.</p>\n\n<p>If he could be any type of animal, Paul would probably be an otter, firstly because they get to experience land and water, and secondly because they always seem to be the animals having the most fun every time he goes to the zoo.</p>\n\n<p>Paul loves anything to do with travel and visiting new places (which probably stems from his dad being a pilot), and has been to all 50 states and over a dozen countries.  He also enjoys movies, music, boats, the mountains, and being around people.</p>\n\n<p>Paul made a living freelance shooting and editing video for commercials, concerts, weddings, and sports before joining the Faith Promise staff in early 2010 as the Student Ministries Program Director.  Pauls passion for youth ministry and love of technology drive him to serve God wholeheartedly in his position using the gifts that God has given him.</p>', 'PaulM@faithpromise.org', '1302', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:04', '2017-09-01 18:25:31', '54b72fe5-4459-497a-b219-28a119fb8b45'),
 ('194', '244', 'en_us', 'Ashley Caldwell', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Ashley', 'Caldwell', 'High School Ministry Assistant', NULL, 'AshleyC@faithpromise.org', '1300', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:04', '2017-09-01 18:25:32', '9c578cce-3292-4618-9ab9-0950cdba450f'),
 ('195', '245', 'en_us', 'Wayne Burress', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Wayne', 'Burress', 'Blount Campus Pastor', '<p>Wayne became the Blount Campus Pastor on March 1st, 2010.  Before joining the staff, he spent almost 20 years designing and developing computer information systems for a couple of Fortune 100 companies.  Regarding his response to Gods call into full-time ministry, he uses this quote from Andy Stanley When God invites me, I do what I can do and trust Him to do what only He can do.<br />\nHe and Angie have been married since 1991 and have enjoyed being a part of the Faith Promise family since 2000.  His primary ministry area has been in adult Groups where hes served as a group leader and coached new leaders.  In addition, he served as a member of the Leadership Team and volunteered in Childrens and First Impressions ministries.\nHe loves to spend time with Angie and their two children, Meredith and Evan.  Sports, reading and time with friends are some of his favorite activities.</p>', 'WayneB@faithpromise.org', '1706', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:05', '2017-09-01 18:25:32', 'f56863eb-43ac-4587-b072-176baecfcbf8'),
 ('196', '246', 'en_us', 'Amy McGehee', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Amy', 'McGehee', 'Assistant to the Associate Pastor of Groups', NULL, 'AmyM@faithpromise.org', '1406', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:05', '2017-09-01 18:25:32', 'e556de83-43b4-419d-8fa5-a24bdbfa3968'),
 ('197', '247', 'en_us', 'Marcy Dorman', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Marcy', 'Dorman', 'Resource Coordinator', NULL, 'MarcyD@faithpromise.org', '1203', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:05', '2017-09-01 18:25:33', '29e40cf1-9b73-40c6-9e86-1ee5f63ec056'),
 ('199', '249', 'en_us', 'Aimee Fair', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Aimee', 'Fair', 'fpKids Preschool Director', NULL, 'AimeeF@faithpromise.org', NULL, 'aimee.g.fair', 'AimeeFair1', 'fairfamilyteam', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 18:25:33', '1c89ff2c-44d0-4632-b2af-da721bcdcfab'),
 ('200', '250', 'en_us', 'Shannan Copland', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Shannan', 'Copland', 'Worship Assistant', '<p>Hi, Im Shannan! I am originally from the SF Bay Area in California, but after high school I joined a touring ministry team based in Knoxville where I met my husband, Nick.  The Lord has kept us here since then and led us to Faith Promise where we are so excited to serve!  I have been at Faith Promise since 2008, the same year Nick and I were married.</p>\n\n<p>With my music background, I immediately became involved in the Worship Ministry as a volunteer and eventually became a volunteer worship leader.  I was brought on staff in 2010 to fill in as the Assistant to the Worship and Creative Arts Director, which, through a series of events led to a permanent position as the Worship Administrative Assistant.</p>\n\n<p>I am a student at Liberty University Online earning my degree in Biblical Studies with a minor in Christian Counseling.  My husband, Nick, is also a student at Tennessee Temple University Online earning his degree in Biblical Studies with a minor in Intercultural Studies (Missions).  We are so excited to finally be done soon as I will graduate this May of 2011 and hell be done in December, but then its seminary for him!</p>\n\n<p><strong>Interesting Fact:</strong> Four months after Nick and I were married, we headed overseas with the International Mission Board and served in Lisbon, Portugal, for eight months and worked with youth partnering with Young Life International.  We both love traveling and ministry and have big hearts for missions!</p>', 'ShannanC@faithpromise.org', '1515', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 18:25:34', 'da8257dc-ce6e-4dca-bfe7-eca575ab6747'),
 ('201', '251', 'en_us', 'Amber Davis', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Amber', 'Davis', 'fpKids Volunteer Coordinator', '<p>I grew up in a home where we put the Lord first. Period. Because my parents were such strong Christian models for me, I became a Christ-follower at a young age and never looked back. I grew up in Knoxville, attended Bearden High School, and then went on to UT to study Journalism and Electronic Media. I started attending Faith Promise in college (2004) and immediately felt drawn to the heart and mission of my new church family-- making it hard to go to hell from East Tennessee.</p>\n\n<p>After graduating college, I moved to the Tri-Cities to take my first TV reporting job at WJHL. It\'s there that I met and fell head over heels in love with my husband. After my contract was up, I came back in Knoxville. Shawn and I married in 2009, and I was thrilled to bring my husband to Faith Promise, the church where I felt at home.</p>\n\n<p>In 2010, the Lord began to work on my heart. At that point, I had been in TV news for six years (locally, I worked for WATE and WVLT) and that was all I knew of the career world. It had been my dream. But I began to feel uneasy. I knew it wasn\'t my heart\'s desire anymore. That was truly scary for such a control freak like me. It was scary until I heard four words from Executive Pastor Josh Whitehead, \"You want a job?\" Yes! If there\'s anything else I\'d rather be doing, it\'s serving my God in ministry! And Family Ministry?! That\'s perfect. I know first-hand the difference a strong foundation makes, and I\'d love to dedicate myself to helping others live that abundant life out at home.</p>\n\n<p>So, that\'s how I went from working in TV to working for Jesus. Let me encourage you to never ignore that still, small voice. He may be calling you to the greatest adventure of your life!</p>\n\n<p>(If you want to join me without making a huge life change... come serve in fpKiDS! What a joy it is!)</p>', 'AmberD@faithpromise.org', '1201', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 18:25:34', 'b829325d-9080-487f-bff5-0a6274000932'),
 ('202', '252', 'en_us', 'Jayson Hines', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Jayson', 'Hines', 'Blount Campus Student Ministry Coordinator', NULL, 'JaysonH@faithpromise.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 18:25:34', 'b6a12614-e85c-4378-b960-7254287440b7'),
 ('203', '253', 'en_us', 'Barry Dunford', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Barry', 'Dunford', 'Live Production Director', '<p>I\'ve been apart of Faith Promise Church since the beginning. I joined the kingdom in 1993, and I started serving in the tech ministry at an early age. At 12, I was running a camera for services, when we met in the mall.</p>\n\n<p>I have bounced around ministries for the past 15 years - from running audio for our kid\'s ministry, doing lights for youth, editing videos for the weekend services, running lights for the weekend services, and designing sets for sermon series. You can say that I have been training for this my whole life. I truly am blessed to work for God and Be able to serve with People that I call my friends and family.</p>\n\n<p>I enjoy playing disc golf and hiking. I also enjoy spending time with my fiance Ashley. I love all types of music, and I listen to anything from Hillsong, Need To Breath, Sara Groves, and Frank Sinatra.</p>\n\n<p>It\'s hard for me to choose my favorite movie, but I like all Tim Burton flicks and most dramas. A few of my favorites are Big Fish, A Beautiful Mind, Edward Scissor Hands, and Good Will Hunting.</p>', 'BarryD@faithpromise.org', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 18:25:35', '7bc29105-bbb8-4813-a968-3625aa05522c'),
 ('205', '255', 'en_us', 'Brenda Moore', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Brenda', 'Moore', 'Receptionist', '<p>I was married to my high school sweetheart for 37 1/2 years. My late husband, Terry, and I served in the ministry together for over 30 years. We have four grown sons and five grandchildren (3 boys and 2 girls).</p>\n\n<p>Terry and Pastor Chris were friends and frequently met together. Terry often said, \"If we didn\'t have a church of our own, we would be at Faith Promise.\" When he was killed in an accident on July 4th of 2009, I realized that I was too distracted to worship at the church my husband and I had started in Clinton, TN. So in the fall of 2009, I began to attend Faith Promise on my own.</p>\n\n<p>I felt God calling me to be a part of Faith Promise\'s staff when I began to feel a restlessness in my spirit at my former job. As I prayed about that restlessness, it became very clear to me that I was to be on staff, but I didn\'t know where God was going to put me. One morning during my quiet time, I felt the restlessness in an even greater way. I asked God, \"What are you trying to tell me? Why am I suddenly so discontent where I am?\"</p>\n\n<p>That very afternoon I got a call from my youngest son who told me he had been on FP\'s website and had found the perfect job for me. I went home, got online, and applied for the Receptionist\'s position. Several interviews and a couple of months later, I received a call that I was being offered the job. I accepted on the spot. I began working at Faith Promise in the fall of 2011. What a blessing it has been to be a part of this team!</p>\n\n<p>I am involved in fpWomen\'s Groups as part of the Leadership Team. I also lead women\'s Bible studies and serve as a baptism assistant.</p>\n\n<p>In my spare time, I love to be with my family-especially with my grandchildren. I also love to read and travel and have a heart for missions.</p>\n\n<p>I am deathly afraid of snakes! I have been known to do a wicked snake dance upon spotting one.</p>', 'BrendaM@faithpromise.org', '1000', 'brenda.d.moore.3', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:11', '2017-09-01 18:25:39', '71c39c0d-4bd1-40ac-a3b3-6798b0cdfe61'),
 ('206', '256', 'en_us', 'Justine Belk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0.00000', '0.00000', NULL, 'Justine', 'Belk', 'fpStudents Apprenticing Coordinator', '<p>Hey! My name is Justine. I started coming to Faith Promise in 2006 and attended with my family until I moved to Birmingham, Alabama, for an Internship program with a Church there. After returning to Knoxville in 2011, my love for Faith Promise grew, and I knew that it was a place I wanted to be a part of.</p>\n\n<p>In the fall of 2011 God answered my prayers and blessed me with the opportunity to serve on staff! A few months later, he opened the door for me to become the Apprentice Coordinator of Student Ministries! The title is just a fancy name for helping people put action to the calling that they feel God has given them.  I know that the Lord has incredible plans for this Church, and I fully believe that He is going to use Faith Promise to make it hard to go to hell, not only from East Tennessee, but also from the nations.</p>\n\n<p>As well as working with our volunteers in fpStudents and helping people get involved here at FPC, I also have a passion for working with young girls to help them realize who they are in Christ. I believe that you don\'t have to be in your twenties or later to find God and truly experience His love.  Because of this passion, I am currently working on my Bachelor\'s in Psychology at the University of Tennessee.</p>\n\n<p>I\'m not sure how God is going to use me exactly; all I know is that I am ready and willing to go wherever he leads.</p>', 'JustineB@faithpromise.org', '1006', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', 'both', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '7', '0', NULL, '2017-09-01 16:42:12', '2017-09-01 18:27:12', '8a89963f-c527-48d1-a445-813a2547bc21'),
