 ('134', '177', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dr. Chris Stephens\",\"slug\":\"chris-stephens\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Pastor Chris was born in Chattanooga, Tennessee to teen parents who split up when he was only three.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>By the age of 22 he was a heavy drug user and dealer. Later that year, Chris woke up in a hospital room after a drug overdose and made a decision to connect with God. This decision was especially amazing since neither Chris nor his family had ever attended church.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Over the next 26 years Chris has been serving God as a speaker and a pastor. He has had the opportunity to speak all over the world and has impacted tens of thousands of lives.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Pastor Chris has written a biographical look at his life and the transformation that took place. The book is called The Climb of Your Life. Chris said if his life could transition from the project to the pulpit; from a life of devastation to an amazing destiny, then so can any life.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>As the Senior Pastor of Faith Promise Church, he has seen thousands find hope and fulfillment in their destiny. Chris says his purpose is to help people recognize and achieve their full potential. He came so close to death and missing all God had for him he now wants to help others find the same purpose in their lives that he has found.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Pastor\'s blog and information about his book can be found at <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/drchrisstephens.com\\\">DrChrisStephens.com<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>You can also connect with Pastor Chris via <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/facebook.com\\/pastorchris\\\">Facebook<\\/a> and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/drchrisstephens\\\">Twitter<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"Pastor@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"pastorchris\",\"16\":\"Chris\",\"25\":\"drchrisstephens\",\"19\":\"Senior Pastor\",\"17\":\"Stephens\",\"26\":[\"22\"],\"22\":\"2000\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"drchrisstephens\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:09', '2017-09-01 16:41:09', 'bca4c048-4b4c-43c9-b4e6-f7cd02dbe943'),
 ('135', '178', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Randy Riggins\",\"slug\":\"randy-riggins\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I have been at FPC since October 2006, and I have been in full time student ministry since 1992.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I enjoy hanging out with my family - wife: Holly, and kids: Shaelee (7), Rylee (5), and Silas (2). I also enjoy running early in the morning (I know, sick huh?) and reading.  Actually, most of my free time gets divided between being an unbelievable husband, watching Rylee annihilate the competition in soccer, attempting to finally beat Shaelee in most any card game, and engaging in deep theological and philosophical debates with Silas.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>One unusual thing about me:  In high school, I played a drum major in a chase scene of a made-for-TV movie.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I grew up most of my life in Texas, but I\\u2019ve also worked in youth ministry in Oklahoma and Louisiana.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Mexican food is my favorite food group, but a great steak dinner is hard to beat.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I enjoy listening to Passion Worship artists (like Crowder and Tomlin), and students enjoy giving me a hard time about enjoying the music of 80\\u2019s artists like Charlie Peacock and Steve Taylor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I graduated from Baylor University with a BA in Communications, and received my Masters in Religious Education from Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I am also a partner with Reach Out Youth Solutions in coaching and mentoring youth pastors\\/workers both nationally and internationally.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"RandyR@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Randy\",\"19\":\"High School Pastor\",\"17\":\"Riggins\",\"22\":\"1301\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:10', '2017-09-01 16:41:10', 'e153b63b-7e6c-4418-b830-7a8113a3f83f'),
 ('136', '179', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Art Jensen\",\"slug\":\"art-jensen\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p><strong>How long have you been at Faith Promise?<\\/strong><br \\/>I was born and raised in San Diego CA.  I am married and have four Children; two boys and two girls.  Before moving to Tennessee I spent four years in Denver.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>When did you come on staff?<\\/strong><br \\/>I have been on staff at Faith promise since June of \\u201907.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>What\\u2019s your favorite hobby?<\\/strong><br \\/>I love sports. My favorite to watch is pro football.  My favorite team is the San Diego Chargers.  And my favorite sport to play is surfing; although the surf in Tennessee is not that great, I will keep trying.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>What is something unusual about you?<\\/strong><br \\/>I have a twin brother\\u2026<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>If you could be any animal, what would it be?<\\/strong><br \\/>If I could be any animal, I would be hmmmm\\u2026 human.  Okay, how about a sheep?  That way I could spend all day with the \\u201cShepherd\\u201d. Okay, okay\\u2026 I would be an eagle, I think it would be cool to be able to fly.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Your favorite food, least favorite food, greatest fear, most embarrassing moment, or nickname growing up.<\\/strong><br \\/>My favorite food is probably steak and potatoes, but I also really like Mexican food, come to think of it, I really like food. My least favorite is shellfish. I am allergic.  My most embarrassing moment is now writing this bio.\\n\\u2026 And my nickname growing up,\\u2026 you will have to ask my wife,\\u2026 and she\'d better not tell you.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"ArtJ@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Art\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Group Ministries\",\"17\":\"Jensen\",\"22\":\"1401\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:10', '2017-09-01 16:41:10', '3802cbee-d018-4514-9f59-6395f896999b'),
 ('137', '181', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gloria Petrowski\",\"slug\":\"gloria-petrowski\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was born in Oak Ridge and have never lived anywhere else. I was raised in a loving Christian home and was saved and baptized at the age of nine. I have one younger sister, Lisa, who lives in Snellville, GA. My parents are both deceased.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I have been married to my awesome husband, Larry, for 36 years. God blessed us with two wonderful children - Justin, 27 and Jenna, 24 - and their equally wonderful spouses - Kara, 26 and Ben, 25. We all serve the Lord here together in various ways in the Worship Ministry of Faith Promise. I began singing in the Cherub Choir at the age of three and have been singing since that time!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I was the first employee hired here when Faith Promise began in 1995. I worked first in finance and membership and then became Pastor Chris\' personal assistant when he joined us in 1996. What a joy it is to serve alongside him and to see all the many miracles God continues to perform here!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I enjoy walking, boating, reading, and especially traveling. If someone says \\\"go\\\", I am always ready! I love hot chocolate-chip cookies and don\'t like greens! I don\'t like heights, but through the years I have learned to conquer that fear somewhat. My nickname growing up was Glory or Gloworm and I can speak pig-Latin really fast!<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"GloriaP@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"gloria.petrowski\",\"16\":\"Gloria\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Senior Pastor\",\"17\":\"Petrowski\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"2000\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"gfpetrowski\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:13', '2017-09-01 16:41:13', '7ed994ee-15bf-45e7-b1fb-89c596bc3451'),
 ('138', '183', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Marti Willen\",\"slug\":\"marti-willen\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I came on staff in 2007, and I absolutely love working at FPC! I have a fantastic life, thanks to my awesome husband, Tim, and our boys, Jacob and Caleb. I love hanging out with my family, reading, singing, and most of all, I love laughing. FP has given me more opportunities than I could have ever dreamed of, and I am so grateful that God led me to a place where He is constantly moving.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"MartiW@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Marti\",\"19\":\"First Impressions & Facilities Director\",\"17\":\"Willen\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1703\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"mwillen\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:16', '2017-09-01 16:41:16', 'cf796bfb-8937-4475-b3d2-d477702435ac'),
 ('139', '184', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jayne Bass\",\"slug\":\"jayne-bass\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"JayneB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jayne\",\"19\":\"Children\'s Services Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Bass\",\"22\":\"1402\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:16', '2017-09-01 16:41:16', '055e7625-02a7-4aba-b672-f20db1bd8354'),
 ('140', '186', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Michele Stephens\",\"slug\":\"michele-stephens\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>My name is Michele but I often answer to \\\"Shay\\\", \\\"Coach\\\", \\\"Mich\\\" and \\\"Mom\\\". These names come from relationships with my husband, co-workers, team members and my children.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I have been married to my best friend, Chris (who happens to be the Sr. Pastor), for 25 years, and we have 3 awesome children Faith, Micah, and Zac as well as a brand new son-in-law, Frankie.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>When I Met Jesus:<\\/strong> I grew up in a godly home where my parents taught me how to study and memorize God?s word, share my faith, and most of all, worship. I began my relationship with Jesus at the age of 8 years old, and what a ride it has been!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>My Calling:<\\/strong> As far as a calling to be a worship leader ? that one kind of snuck up on me. I had grown up in a musical home where both of my parents lead in worship through singing and playing the guitar. My dad would make me play the piano and sing (at the time I hated it ? I was scared to death!) in church, during mission trips, or anywhere else he could find. After all those experiences, I guess I should have seen what was coming down the pike.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I met my sweetheart at what was then called the BSU at UT-Chattanooga. He was going to be a preacher ? me a preacher?s wife?! But now I know that God had prepared me my whole life to be Chris? helpmate and ministry partner. I loved working in different areas as we began our ministry, but it seemed no matter what ministry it was, worship was at the heart.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>As the ministry assistant to the Worship Pastor at Faith Promise Church, they asked me to fill in when he left until they could find someone. Well, that was almost 9 years ago. God has confirmed to me over and over that He called me and put me where I am today ? I would have never believed it, and there is no way I could do what I do without the anointing and favor of the Lord.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Favorite Music:<\\/strong> Anything Hillsong, anything Chris Tomlin, and ?clean? classic rock. (I am an ?80s girl.)<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Hobbies:<\\/strong> Anything with my family, scrapbooking, and photography.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"MicheleS@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"michele7317\",\"16\":\"Michele\",\"25\":\"michele7317\",\"19\":\"Global Worship & Creative Arts Pastor\",\"17\":\"Stephens\",\"26\":[\"22\",\"27\"],\"22\":\"1501\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"michele7317\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:20', '2017-09-01 16:41:20', '604b5593-9800-4992-8383-acc3c3866ec7'),
 ('141', '187', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Caroline Ervin\",\"slug\":\"caroline-ervin\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Caroline Ervin has been on staff as the Membership Director since September 2006.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She attended Samford University in Birmingham, Alabama, and graduated with a bachelor\\u2019s degree in Journalism and Mass Communication.  Caroline met her husband, Brad Ervin (who is also on staff at FPC), in college, and they were married in 2003.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Caroline enjoys traveling and going on mission trips to China and Africa.  She also loves to read, shop, and spend time with her small group.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Her biggest annoyance is when people ask her when she and Brad are going to start having kids.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"CarolineE@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Caroline\",\"19\":\"Membership Director\",\"17\":\"Ervin\",\"22\":\"1001\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:20', '2017-09-01 16:41:20', 'c9394b0d-5c69-40df-b192-4c5ed2398aec'),
 ('142', '188', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Nancy Bachor\",\"slug\":\"nancy-bachor\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>My husband David and I started attending Faith Promise in October 2004. I came on staff in early 2007, and I am so humbled that God allows me to be even the tiniest part of what He is doing here at FPC!!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In 1998 David, our two sons Sean and Ryan, and I set out from south Florida to our Promised Land, with hurricane Georges traveling along beside us.  Our little family of four that moved to East Tennessee has grown in the ten years that we have been here.  We have added to our family a lovely daughter-in-law, Christy, and two precious grandchildren, Colin and Audrey. We are blessed more than we could hope or imagine!!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I love to spend time with my family, especially the grandkids, truly a gift from God!!  I have been classified by my husband as not just a book lover but a book collector.  I love to read - especially anything that draws me closer to the Lord. I also enjoy Sudoku, hiking, camping, geocaching, target practice, and riding the motorcycle with my hubby.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My favorite food? It might be easier to list what I don\\u2019t like... sushi, rhubarb, and liver.  Everything else is my favorite especially anything Italian, Mexican, Asian, Mediterranean, Cajun, or American.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Unusual? Well, I would have to say \\u201cyes, I am\\u201d but that\\u2019s not what you meant.  I want the truth, no matter how painful just give it to me straight, no fluff and please, please, do not beat around the bush!!! Oh yeah, and check out the left pinky toe when I\\u2019m wearing flip-flops or barefoot.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Facebook at Nancy Bachor<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"NancyB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Nancy\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Membership Director\",\"17\":\"Bachor\",\"22\":\"1013\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:20', '2017-09-01 16:41:20', '1881597d-2eeb-4317-9e98-8c13c830f085'),
 ('143', '190', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Aaron Goin\",\"slug\":\"aaron-goin\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Aaron Goin joined the staff of Faith Promise as Finance Director in August 2007, and in January 2011, Aaron took on the role of Chief Financial Officer. In this role he gets to work alongside great teams in Finance, Human Resources, Information Technology, Communications, Next Steps, and Facilities.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Aaron and his wife Kerri were married in 2000. Their daughter Gracie was born in April 2006 and their son Mason was born in August of 2009. They love all things Disney, Dollywood, the beach, and any other kind of family adventure.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In 2002, Aaron graduated from the University of Tennessee with a bachelor\'s degree in Finance. He received his Master of Business Administration degree in December 2010. Before joining the staff of Faith Promise, he worked for five years at Oak Ridge National Laboratory as a Subcontract Administrator.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>\\\"It has been an amazing journey to watch Faith Promise grow and to play a small part in that growth. Can\'t wait to see what God does as we continue to reach the world for Him.\\\"<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"AaronG@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Aaron\",\"19\":\"Chief Financial Officer\",\"17\":\"Goin\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1602\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"aarongoin\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '2017-09-01 16:41:23', 'aa2d38a0-2570-43a8-8c0d-03222521ad89'),
 ('144', '191', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Robin Floyd\",\"slug\":\"robin-floyd\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>My family has attended Faith Promise, off and on, since they began meeting in the old church in Oak Ridge.  We served in other churches in between but kept returning to FPC and have been here since 2006.   I began working at Faith Promise in April \\u201908.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I love to read and spend time with my family.  I have 2 daughters. Chelsea is 14 and Lauren is 11, and their schedules take up most of my time outside work.  I have been married for 15 years to my husband, Greg.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I homeschooled both of my children until last year.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Any food is my favorite, except chicken livers, and I have a HUGE fear of heights.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"rfloyd@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Robin\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Financial Director\",\"17\":\"Floyd\",\"22\":\"1600\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '5707dbdc-9283-4af8-bf66-65654de78b40'),
 ('145', '192', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Chris Cox\",\"slug\":\"chris-cox\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Amy and I started attending Faith Promise in 2004. We were married January 2005, and we have two children, Lexie and Brayden. I\'ve been on staff since January 2007.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Random Facts:<\\/strong> I grew up in Oliver Springs, TN, and I was a junior olympic in white water kayaking.  I like to fish, play golf, and spend time with my family.  I will eat just about any kind of food, but my favorite is lasagna. My wife can whip me at Guitar Hero. Some people may not know this, but I almost pass out whenever I see blood.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"ChrisC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Chris\",\"19\":\"Facilities Director\",\"17\":\"Cox\",\"22\":\"1703\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '1081d72d-9bc4-4fea-a495-504caf804cf2'),
 ('146', '193', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Adrianne Adams\",\"slug\":\"adrianne-adams\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"AdrianneA@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Adrianne\",\"19\":\"Housekeeper\",\"17\":\"Adams\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '2017-09-01 16:41:23', '97ffa880-8c58-4726-bb1b-162beabda3f4'),
 ('147', '194', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Adam McCue\",\"slug\":\"adam-mccue\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hey everyone\\u2026 I\\u2019m Adam!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I have been part of Faith Promise Church since early 2000. Started volunteering Day 1 (somewhat under my own volition). Serving is BIG here, and it\\u2019s a blast!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I volunteered in Worship for a long time.  That\'s where I learned to play some music\\u2026 enough to make me dangerous, anyway.  After seven years or so, when they realized I wouldn\\u2019t leave, I was brought on staff. Somewhere in there (2006), I graduated from UTK with a Finance\\/Economics degree, which I use everyday.  Hahaha.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Hobbies\\u2026? Uhhhhh\\u2026 I like to play golf, soccer, and most other sports. I love to snow ski! I enjoy going to restaurants with my fianc\\u00e9, Mary Beth Rader, and hanging out with her in general.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Unusual\\u2026? well, I was a competitive power tumbler during the high school years. We went all over the south-east to meets and competitions and stuff\\u2026 super fun!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Hit me up on Facebook, or find me after a service and introduce yourself, I LOVE that!!!<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"AdamM@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Adam\",\"19\":\"Worship Associate\",\"17\":\"McCue\",\"22\":\"1505\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:24', '2017-09-01 16:41:24', 'd73b10eb-30a0-4be8-a178-5671051b40ed'),
 ('148', '195', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Mia Hannahs\",\"slug\":\"mia-hannahs\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Mia joined the FPC staff in August of 2005, after meeting Pastor Chris at Ripley\\u2019s Believe It or Not in Gatlinburg. She has a passion for early childhood education and has been working with preschoolers and their families for twenty years.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She grew up in a big family that enjoyed music and art and is the last of seven kids. Now, she is the mother to Parker [an aspiring artist], Tyler [a self-proclaimed sci-fi fanatic] and Kylie [who loves horseback riding].<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She enjoys singing, reading, camping, and creating. Her greatest hope-  helping multitudes of families and volunteers develop a strong spiritual foundation in young children. Her greatest fear- being trapped in a car underwater.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"MiaH@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Mia\",\"19\":\"Blount Campus fpKids Director\",\"17\":\"Hannahs\",\"22\":\"1200\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:24', '2017-09-01 16:41:24', 'bcb4c139-49db-4932-8f65-f9634b58cd4a'),
 ('149', '196', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Pam Bakker\",\"slug\":\"pam-bakker\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Pam has been at Faith Promise since June 2001 and came on staff December 2007.  Her favorite hobbies include cooking and reading.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Her favorite food is Mexican or pasta, least favorite is veggies, and greatest fear is not making a difference for Jesus.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Something unusual about yourself?<\\/strong><br \\/> I grew up inn Southern California, and I am the mother of twins, born by surrogacy (my sister).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>If you could be any animal, what would it be?<\\/strong><br \\/>A bird.  I\'d love to travel around and see everything!<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"PamB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Pam\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the PromiseKids Director\",\"17\":\"Bakker\",\"22\":\"1201\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:24', '2017-09-01 16:41:24', 'bb1faf1e-3185-4363-8cbc-1d8caab06993'),
 ('150', '197', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jennifer Loveday\",\"slug\":\"jennifer-loveday\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Among her other attributes, Jennifer is a fan of people (all shapes, sizes, ages, and backgrounds).  After five years on staff at Faith Promise, she currently works with people of the smaller variety in our K-5th grade Children\\u2019s Ministry (KidK\\u2019nex) program.  Originally from Knoxville, Jennifer returned home after several treks in professional theaters, tours, and ministries.  She holds a degree in Communication and Theater Arts from the University of the Cumberlands.  As KidK\\u2019nex Programming Director, she incorporates her love for Christ, children and creative storytelling each weekend into a Large Group teaching environment.  She enjoys smiles,  laughter, energy, fun, insight, and sincerity from all our wonderful Faith Promise kids.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"JenniferL@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jennifer\",\"19\":\"KidK\'nex Programming Director\",\"17\":\"Loveday\",\"22\":\"1102\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:25', '2017-09-01 16:41:25', '43b4d411-3192-4e4d-a81c-21a13ffac05a'),
 ('151', '198', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Susan Troop\",\"slug\":\"susan-troop\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Susan Troop has been on staff part time since October of 2006.  She served as the Mother\\u2019s Day Out Director prior to taking the position of Kids Hope USA Director.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She attended the University of Vermont, where she earned her bachelor\\u2019s degree in Elementary Education.  She has ten years of teaching experience.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Susan met her husband and was married in Orlando, FL in 1993.  While growing up in Vermont, she has also lived in Florida, Kansas, and Virginia before settling in Knoxville.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Susan is the mother of three girls and two dogs.  She enjoys shopping, naps, and special times with the family.  She also enjoys going on mission trips and has especially loved traveling to South Africa.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"SusanT@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Susan\",\"19\":\"Kid\\u2019s Hope Coordinator \",\"17\":\"Troop\",\"22\":\"1202\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:25', '2017-09-01 16:41:25', '0bb9eb3d-dddc-4c6d-9cd0-a35029629c14'),
 ('152', '199', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Caitie Maylott\",\"slug\":\"caitie-maylott\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"CaitieM@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Caitie\",\"19\":\"Caitie Maylott\",\"17\":\"Maylott\",\"22\":\"1203\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:25', '2017-09-01 16:41:25', 'f75a9814-a48a-42cb-984b-1f13b13322e8'),
 ('153', '200', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Cheryl Christensen\",\"slug\":\"cheryl-christensen\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Cheryl and her family have been at Faith Promise since 2003, and she came on staff in January 2008.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Favorite Hobbies:<\\/strong><br \\/> I like to travel, hang out with my boyfriend of 25 years, go to the movies, and do girl things with my daughters!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Something Unusual:<\\/strong><br \\/> My husband was in the Navy for 20 years, and I was the command liaison for the submarine, USS Tennessee, for 4 years.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>If you could be any animal, what would it be?<\\/strong><br \\/> I would be a dog! They give unconditional love, and they get to eat, sleep, and play all day.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Life Calling:<\\/strong><br \\/> I love missions, and Greg and I intend to go into full time missions one day. Every trip I\'ve ever been on has been great! I have been to Thailand 2 times, Macau, and Capetown.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"CherylC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Cheryl\",\"19\":\"Administrative Support Assistant\",\"17\":\"Christensen\",\"22\":\"1000\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:26', '2017-09-01 16:41:26', '9a902a8d-78e8-4b6e-b5d9-31456ccaa754'),
 ('154', '201', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Teresa Merritt\",\"slug\":\"teresa-merritt\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Teresa is a Knoxville native with a BS degree from UT. She has three grown children (a son and two married daughters). She and her husband, Mark, have been members at Faith Promise Church since 2005. Teresa is passionate about young people finding their God-designed purpose in life and living the abundant life that Jesus promises those who seek Him with their whole heart.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>HOBBY:<\\/strong> READING<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>UNUSUAL:<\\/strong> I love microbiology &amp; biochemistry<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>ANIMAL:<\\/strong> A fat, lazy cat (one that could read, preferably)<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>FAVORITE FOOD:<\\/strong> Vanilla ice cream (not because it\\u2019s boring but because of all the ways it can be changed!)<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"TeresaM@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Teresa\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the High School Pastor\",\"17\":\"Merritt\",\"22\":\"1300\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:26', '2017-09-01 16:41:26', '7533cef9-e883-441c-b182-084e90981acd'),
 ('155', '203', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Matt Grimes\",\"slug\":\"matt-grimes\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Matt grew up in Alabama and went to college at Samford University in Birmingham, where he graduated with a degree in religious studies. He also holds a Master\'s degree in Christian Education from New Orleans Seminary. Matt has served in student ministry at Faith Promise Church since 2005 where he established and built the middle school ministry before taking over all students in 2013.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In addition to his work at Faith Promise and his time traveling and speaking at conferences and events, Matt also serves on staff with Ken Davis and Michael Hyatt as a Communication Coach for Dynamic Communicators International.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Matt is married to Carmen, and they have a beautiful daughter, Elin who was born in 2011.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"9\"],\"21\":\"MattG@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"matt.grimes.7\",\"16\":\"Matt\",\"25\":\"themattgrimes\",\"19\":\"Blount Campus Pastor\",\"17\":\"Grimes\",\"26\":[\"23\"],\"22\":\"1706\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"mattgrimes\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:29', '2017-09-01 16:41:29', '68892868-499e-43ba-8a93-57bb976b1c99'),
 ('156', '205', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Brad Ervin\",\"slug\":\"brad-ervin\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1462510800,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Brad Ervin is the Pastor of Outreach and Missions at Faith Promise. He joined the staff in Nov 2007, and he and his wife Caroline have been attending faith promise since February of 2006. Brad is a huge Vol fan and loves sports in general. He graduated with a BS in Business Marketing from Samford University in 2001.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Hobbies include: reading (Tolkien\\/Ayn Rand\\/Robert Jordan some favs), travel, music (especially British Rock), movies, broadway and west end musicals, and sucking the marrow out of life. He is also an accomplished break dancer and pole vaulter.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Facebook him Brad Ervin, twitter: BradErvin and myspace: Volcrazy.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"BradE@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"bradervin\",\"16\":\"Brad\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Outreach and Missions\",\"17\":\"Ervin\",\"26\":[\"26\",\"29\"],\"22\":\"1405\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"bradervin\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:30', '2017-09-01 16:41:30', '105974ec-51e5-4e94-ad7d-4731df54bc6a'),
 ('157', '207', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jaclyn Holloway\",\"slug\":\"jaclyn-holloway\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>A beach girl at heart that fell in love with the mountains, Jaclyn moved to Knoxville from Virginia Beach in 2005. Jaclyn has a B.S. in Communications from the University of Tennessee with a focus on video production. She has been a part of the worship ministry staff since 2011 and feels extremely blessed to be part of such a talented and creative team. She enjoys film producing and acting as part of her ministry, especially when humor is involved.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>When she goes home, she gets to play her favorite role: a wife and mother. Her husband, Phil Holloway is also on staff in the worship ministry as the Vocal Director. They are blessed with two very active boys, Jameson and Jude. Favorite family hobbies include dance parties with Yo Gabba Gabba, drag racing hot wheels, and extreme water balloon fights. Follow their adventures on twitter: @HollowayJaclyn, snapchat: jhollaback, Instagram: jholloway1120<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"JaclynH@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jaclyn\",\"25\":\"jholloway1120\",\"19\":\"fpCreative Project Manager\",\"17\":\"Holloway\",\"26\":[\"27\"],\"22\":\"1503\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"HollowayJaclyn\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '4dea0715-fa19-4496-9451-738d7fe9207a'),
 ('158', '208', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Debbie McChesney\",\"slug\":\"debbie-mcchesney\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>On November 18th, 1999, during her freshman year of college at the University of the Cumberlands, Debbie surrendered her heart and life to Christ. In 2004, she married the love of her life, Adam, and they began attending Faith Promise in 2005.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Both Debbie and Adam serve in the worship ministry, and Debbie joined the worship staff in November of 2007. She is the proud mother of a beautiful little girl, Abigail, and enjoys karaoke, scrapbooking, and spending time with her family.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"DebbieM@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Debbie\",\"19\":\"Worship Assistant\",\"17\":\"McChesney\",\"22\":\"1503\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '4581e4eb-9593-4cfd-bf05-a1cbc697494a'),
 ('159', '209', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Nolan Smith\",\"slug\":\"nolan-smith\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"nolan@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Nolan\",\"19\":\"Worship Technical Director\",\"17\":\"Smith\",\"22\":\"1504\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '2017-09-01 16:41:33', '37820998-2dc3-4ee0-a1ea-213dbce8a7f2'),
 ('160', '211', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kyle Gilbert\",\"slug\":\"kyle-gilbert\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Kyle came on staff at Faith Promise Church in October 2008 as the Pastor of Communications. He oversees web technology, graphic design, the Internet Campus, and helping get the word out about our church.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>He and his wife, Keri, were married in 1999 and haven\'t owned a TV since then. They have four crazy-awesome kids, including a set of twins.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Kyle has gone skydiving, and he once went scuba diving in the Black Sea after five minutes of instruction (in Russian).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>For fun, Kyle loves to play disc golf and racquetball, and he plays both poorly but with enthusiasm.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>You can keep up with Kyle on his blog at <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/kylesrandom.com\\\">KylesRandom.com<\\/a> or <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/kylegilbert\\\">follow him on Twitter<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[],\"21\":\"KyleG@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"kylegilbert\",\"16\":\"Kyle\",\"25\":\"kylegilbert\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Communications & Internet Campus Pastor\",\"17\":\"Gilbert\",\"26\":[\"23\",\"27\"],\"22\":\"1704\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"kylegilbert\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:36', '2017-09-01 16:41:36', '08c1901a-7db3-4007-a1fb-2eabf99ec335'),
 ('161', '213', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Sid Spiva\",\"slug\":\"sid-spiva\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Sid is a lifelong resident of Clinton and Anderson County. After working in Anderson County Schools for 32 years as a High School Teacher and Principal, Sid entered full time ministry in 2008. He joined the Faith Promise staff when the Anderson County Campus opened in 2013.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Sid and his wife Judy of 40 years have two outstanding sons, two wonderful daughter-in-laws, and two awesome grandsons.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>He enjoys traveling, riding motorcycles, music, and spending time with family.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"13\"],\"21\":\"SidS@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"sid.spiva\",\"16\":\"Sid\",\"19\":\"Multisite Facilities Director\",\"17\":\"Spiva\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"27\":[]}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:39', '2017-09-01 16:41:39', '820326a5-db14-4508-8481-e519d0d23a85'),
 ('162', '215', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Emily Carringer\",\"slug\":\"emily-carringer\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1475211600,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>My husband, Chuck, and I have been at Faith Promise Church since the very first service at the Garden Plaza Hotel in Oak Ridge. However, I didn\'t join the FPC staff until 2003.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>It has been an adventure ever since. You really never know what each day will hold. We have two great kids that have grown up at FPC. Zach is 14 and Maggie is 11. When we\'re not at church, we love eating out and hanging out together as a family.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I love to read, have fun, and laugh a lot, usually at myself. One of the coolest parts about what I get to do is to help others be a part of the Worship Ministry and serve where they are passionate.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"EmilyC@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"emily.carringer\",\"16\":\"Emily\",\"25\":\"emilycarringer\",\"19\":\"Production Pastor\",\"17\":\"Carringer\",\"26\":[\"27\"],\"22\":\"1500\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"emilycarringer\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:41', '2017-09-01 16:41:41', '018d0046-31fa-4a7b-84a8-e95ac53f4605'),
 ('163', '217', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jennifer Patrick\",\"slug\":\"jennifer-patrick\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1481608800,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Jennifer has been attending Faith Promise Church since January 2002. Soon afterwards, she and her family attended a small group, and that began her love for small group ministry. She started out as a volunteer in small group ministry, and she\'s been on staff since 2005.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In her free time, she and her husband, Rob love to spend time at the lake with friends and family and make frequent visits to the Smoky mountains.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"JenniferP@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"jennifer.c.patrick.94\",\"16\":\"Jennifer\",\"25\":\"jenniferlpatrick\",\"19\":\"Group Assimilation Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Patrick\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"22\":\"1403\",\"27\":[]}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:45', '2017-09-01 16:41:45', 'db67c23d-c17c-41b4-afbf-1abe088a7799'),
 ('164', '219', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Heather Burson\",\"slug\":\"heather-burson\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1486965600,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi, I\'m Heather. I\'m a native East Tennessean, graduate of the University of Tennessee, and a die-hard Vols fan. My husband, Mike, and I enjoy travel, college football, and a little friendly competition now and again.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>On staff since 2007, I love being a member of the Communications Team (part of the Admin staff) and a keeper of the Faith Promise brand. One of my favorite things about designing at Faith Promise is the variety of projects that come my way, but by far the best thing is that is I get to be part of an awesome team that is impacting the world for Christ.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"HeatherB@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"heatherburson\",\"16\":\"Heather\",\"19\":\"Graphic Designer\",\"17\":\"Burson\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1014\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"heatherburson\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:48', '2017-09-01 16:41:48', '5ff7c1bd-9550-4e5b-8cd4-8eef7c60ec82'),
 ('165', '221', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Drew Wells\",\"slug\":\"drew-wells\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Drew began attending Faith Promise in 1995. In 2001, he started as an intern for the Student Ministry and eventually came on full-time in 2003 as the Student Ministry Program Director, the Pastor of Young Adults in 2007, and after some brief training on the swamp planet of Dagobah, returned to staff in 2017 as the Pastor of Discipleship.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Drew married his beautiful bride Sandy in 2005 and is the proud father of two sons, Justus and Theo. Before becoming a family man, he graduated college from Pellissippi State Community College with an AS in General Sciences in 2003 and from Tusculum College with BS in Organizational Management in 2006.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Aside from being an avid reader, aspiring writer, and closet cinephile, he also enjoys using his vacation days to sit front row at Nissan or Wrigley Field to watch his beloved Titans and Cubs.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"DrewW@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Drew\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Discipleship\",\"17\":\"Wells\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"22\":\"1302\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"dreWells\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:50', '2017-09-01 16:41:50', '9235aa5b-9ec6-4497-82cf-104365633a0e'),
 ('166', '222', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Evan Crass\",\"slug\":\"evan-crass\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Evan serves as a pastor in the groups office at Faith Promise Church. Although Evan rolled on staff in July 2008, he has been a part of FPC since the very beginning. Prior to becoming a staff member, he served in various areas, including the Leadership Team and the Management Team and has continuously served as a group leader since returning home for graduate school in 1998.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Evan\\u2019s background includes working with start-ups and emerging companies, and he continues to consult with these companies, specifically in the areas of operations and finance. It is this same passion to see new companies grow that drives him to create and nurture new and creative groups to connect people with God and others.  These groups form the foundation for the church\\u2019s diverse offering of interest groups.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>He and his wife, Marta, were married in May 2000. They have a daughter, Kate, who was added to the family in May 2007, and a son, Andrew, who was born in December 2009. The extended family includes the hundreds of people who have been a part of their group over the years.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>You can connect with Evan on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/evancrass\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Facebook<\\/a> or on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/evancrass\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Twitter<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"EvanC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Evan\",\"19\":\"Associate Pastor of Groups\",\"17\":\"Crass\",\"22\":\"1404\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:50', '2017-09-01 16:41:50', '49ae444f-8f1d-4171-a602-d4688dfd15aa'),
 ('167', '223', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Phil Bledsoe\",\"slug\":\"phil-bledsoe\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p><strong>About Me:<\\/strong> I was born in Tallahassee, Florida, and was raised in Georgia - mostly around the Atlanta area. My family was a very strong Christian family and all of us were involved in the church from an early age.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I moved to Nashville in 1998 to pursue a degree in Music Business and Recording. I was in a band but transitioned to the production side of things when I moved to Nashville. Originally, I was focused on a future in studio work, but God continually gave me more opportunities in live production.  I began working for artists with whom I had played in my performing days and those jobs quickly opened more opportunities deeper into the Christian Music Industry. I spent a few years in audio, a few years in lighting and transitioned back to Audio with the added responsibility of tour managing for bands such as Skillet and Tree63. For the past 7 years I\'ve taken off in the fall to production manage a 15-20 band traveling music festival called SHOUTfest, showcasing many major industry headliners such as Third Day and Newsboys.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I was married in 2002 to my beautiful bride, Shanell. She is originally from the Knoxville area but we met at MTSU in 2000. We travelled together for years until she launched a successful photography business in 2007. My decision to leave the glamour of the road is based around our great desire to start a family. We\'ve been blessed with the opportunity to join the FP family and are looking forward to growing our family internally and externally!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Interesting Fact:<\\/strong> Shanell and I took a two-month honeymoon and travelled the entire US and Canada (including Hawaii).<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"PhilB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Phil\",\"19\":\"Technical Director\",\"17\":\"Bledsoe\",\"22\":\"1510\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '59d1521f-6d6a-4ba9-9520-b61ef4e9c0b3'),
 ('168', '224', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Krista McBroom\",\"slug\":\"krista-mcbroom\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Krista has attended Faith Promise since May 2007.  She first came on staff as a summer intern for the student ministry and has been on staff since January 2008.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She attended Carson Newman College where she got her degree in Child and Family Studies.  She has also started working on her Masters in Christian Education.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She likes to read, scrapbook, and be outside.  But her favorite thing to do is writing poetry and devotionals.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Something unusual about her is that she is left handed.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"krista@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Krista\",\"19\":\"Receptionist\",\"17\":\"McBroom\",\"22\":\"1000\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '2017-09-01 16:41:51', 'e100684f-97f3-4103-bea2-6282e4774f9b'),
 ('169', '225', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Justin Truluck\",\"slug\":\"justin-truluck\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Born in Farragut, I was raised as a second generation Christian and was brought up in and around the church in all elements of life. At the age of 13, with no understanding of how things worked, I was put behind a sound board to fill a need for the church I was serving in and have never looked back.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In 2004 I graduated from Farragut High school and joined the staff at M&amp;L Sound where my passion and understanding for all things audio continued to grow.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>During my final years in grade school, I decided that I needed to experience the world in a new and truly unique way, so I opted to study abroad and continue developing my understanding of God and his plan. I did this by attending Southern Cross College in Sydney Australia where I graduated in 2008 with a Bachelors of Theology in Christian Ministry. During that time I continued to serve God through my involvement in a church production department and had the opportunity to be involved in many large-scale events which continued to build my understanding of all aspects of Production.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Today I am continuing to grow personally and corporately and I can\'t wait to see what God has in store for the future.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"JustinT@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Justin\",\"19\":\"Live Production Director\",\"17\":\"Truluck\",\"22\":\"1515\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '58748cdc-f652-4e78-a53d-135f1555368d'),
 ('170', '226', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tanya Tumminello\",\"slug\":\"tanya-tumminello\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"TanyaT@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Tanya\",\"19\":\"KidK\\u2019nex Ministry Assistant\",\"17\":\"Tumminello\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '2017-09-01 16:41:51', '241424d4-acbf-40b2-8d0b-5e77f1fd4ab4'),
 ('171', '227', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Matt James\",\"slug\":\"matt-james\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I am a Geek. Now, a lot of people associate geekdom with those guys in High School who had absolutely zero people skills. Those are nerds. Geeks are the hybrids who get along and enjoy the company of people as well as the company of technology. Therefore, I am a Geek.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\'m overly educated with a BS degree in Television Production from MTSU (Go Chicken Horses! err... Raiders!) as well as surviving a five-year apprenticeship in the IBEW. So, I\'m either an Electrician who dabbles in Video Production or a Video Producer who dabbles in Electrical work.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Hobbies include reading, home improvement, four wheeling in my Jeep, Movies, Music, as well as a select few TV shows. Reading is usually something Science Fiction flavored. I\'ve also branched spiritual growth books since I became a Christian. Favorite books include Dune, Blue like Jazz, and Velvet Elvis. I also have a weakness for Stephen King\\u2019s writing.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My taste in movies is all over the map - from classics such as \\u2018Metropolis\\u2019 to more modern works like \\u2018Coraline\\u2019. Musical tastes are also all over the map... From Rock, to Classical, to Bluegrass - I\'ll listen to anything. TV shows such as Lost, Eli Stone, NCIS, Good Eats, and Battlestar Galactica (the new one) are among those set to record on my DVR.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\'ve been a member of Faith Promise since 2002 when I accepted Jesus as my Lord and Savior. Shortly after that, I started volunteering in the Video Ministry. Since then, I\'ve I joined the staff as Video Director. In what I hope is an indicator of things to come, my first three days on staff were snow days.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>If you want, look me up on Facebook or just send me an email. I\'m always up for email, something about being a geek....<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Or, check out my blog: <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/realtater.blogspot.com\\\">realtater.blogspot.com<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"MattJ@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Matt\",\"19\":\"Video Director\",\"17\":\"James\",\"22\":\"1520\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:52', '2017-09-01 16:41:52', 'd7338f6a-dfff-407d-8b38-dbbcbe14c23f'),
 ('172', '228', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Roger Owens\",\"slug\":\"roger-owen\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1439933624,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"RogerO@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Roger\",\"19\":\"Campbell Campus Groups Pastor & Missions Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Owens\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:52', '2017-09-01 16:41:52', '82b4a794-a96b-4070-a633-4561d083ada8'),
 ('173', '230', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Zac Stephens\",\"slug\":\"zac-stephens\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"128\"],\"21\":\"ZacS@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"zac.stephens.71\",\"16\":\"Zac\",\"25\":\"fps_pastorzac\",\"19\":\"Farragut Campus Pastor\",\"17\":\"Stephens\",\"26\":[\"23\"],\"22\":\"1304\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"fps_pastorzac\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:55', '2017-09-01 16:41:55', '2a7a3566-ef17-4100-9709-33fee4d6d64a'),
 ('174', '232', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dr. Chuck Carringer\",\"slug\":\"chuck-carringer\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>In my role as Pastor of Leadership Development and Stewardship I partner with staff and volunteers to increase leadership capacity and stewardship across Faith Promise. From 2009-2014 I served as Pastor of Family Ministry. Prior to joining the staff I served for 24 years in public schools. From 1990-2009 I was part of the faculty at Oak Ridge High School serving in a variety of roles including: teacher, coach, vice principal, athletic director, and principal.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My wife Emily, of 25 years, and I have been members of Faith Promise since the church began. I volunteered in a number of ministry areas including serving as an elder, student ministry, school of leaders, and membership classes.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In addition to my role at Faith Promise I provide executive coaching to business leaders. I have a doctorate in executive leadership as well as being a John Maxwell Team Certified Coach, Speaker and Trainer. In addition to executive coaching, I speak frequently to business teams and organizations.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I enjoy family time, and Em, Zach (20 years old), and Maggie (17 years old). We love traveling, especially to the beach! In addition to family fun I enjoy sports, reading, exercising, and time with friends.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Follow Chuck on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/chuckcarringer\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\">Twitter<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/chuckcarringer\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Facebook<\\/a>, or <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.chuckcarringer.com\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">his blog<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"ChuckC@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"chuckcarringer\",\"16\":\"Chuck\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Leadership Development & Stewardship\",\"17\":\"Carringer\",\"26\":[\"22\"],\"22\":\"1101\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"chuckcarringer\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:57', '2017-09-01 16:41:57', '64853d54-47ef-44e3-b5a3-c65b5d6ac89f'),
 ('175', '233', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Melanie Goodman\",\"slug\":\"melanie-goodman\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>We started attending Faith Promise Church in 2007, and I joined the awesome Faith Promise Family Ministry Staff in February 2009.  I am very blessed to be given the opportunity to serve God doing the very thing God has equipped me for!  I am the assistant to the Middle School Pastor and love working with the student ministry staff and students.  I have an overwhelming desire to help teenage students experience a personal relationship with God and help equip them with the tools they need to make good choices that will impact their lives forever.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\'ve been happily married to my husband Jonathan Goodman since January 18, 1992.  I\'m the luckiest lady alive to be married to the love of my life and best friend!!  Along with Jonathan came a special blessing, my step-son Justin who I love very much.  Together Jonathan and I have two children, Zeke and Darah.  We love spending time together as a family.  We camp, ride bikes, run, and love anything that involves a beach.  We have fun doing anything as long as were together.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I was extremely blessed for the privilege and support of my husband to be able to stay home to raise my children for 15 years.  During that time I worked part time as a children\'s ministry director at a previous church and also as a substitute teacher.  I spent numerous hours volunteering and loving every minute I spent being with Zeke and Darah.  I am humbled that God would loan such precious children to me so I could be their mom!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Hobbies:  I love to read anything that helps me to grow spiritually, and my guilty pleasure: Karen Kingsbury novels.  I love to run!  Yes I said it, I love to run!  When I\'ve had a stressful day, running always sets me at ease.  I use this time to meditate on all God has for me - except for the times I\'m begging God to get me through the next mile!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Favorite bible verse: Search me, O God, and know my heart; test me and know my anxious thoughts.  See if there is any offensive way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.  Psalm 139: 23-24<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"MelanieG@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Melanie\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Middle School Pastor\",\"17\":\"Goodman\",\"22\":\"1305\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:58', '2017-09-01 16:41:58', '78d6e5d8-aa60-423f-b78c-e94233b63e56'),
 ('176', '234', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Deneen Lambert\",\"slug\":\"deneen-lambert\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1442552400,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"DeneenL@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"deneen.lambert\",\"16\":\"Deneen\",\"25\":\"deneenl\",\"19\":\"Finance Assistant\",\"17\":\"Lambert\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1600\",\"24\":\"deneenl14\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:41:58', '2017-09-01 16:41:58', '3ff853de-287c-4b10-8540-3c951e5c74c2'),
 ('177', '236', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Joe Filipowicz\",\"slug\":\"joe-filipowicz\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was born in Toledo Ohio but moved to Knoxville in 1989.  While I like Tennessee Football I am a die hard Ohio State fan!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My wife Donna and I started dating in high school and have been married for {{ \'1994-10-01\' | age }} awesome years. We have two kids \\u2013 Katie, {{ \'1995-10-01\' | age }} and Brandon, {{ \'1998-09-01\' | age }}.  Katie is a sophomore at the University of Tennessee and Brandon is a Junior in high school. They are both involved with the church and we couldn\\u2019t be prouder of who they have become!!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I have been working at Faith Promise Church for {{ \'2009-09-01\' | age }} years and love coming to work everyday!  I enjoy Basketball, soccer, football and... well pretty much anything that\\u2019s competitive.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"JoeF@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"joe.filipowicz.jr\",\"16\":\"Joe\",\"25\":\"joeflip\",\"19\":\"IT Director\",\"17\":\"Filipowicz\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1605\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"joeflip2\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:00', '2017-09-01 16:42:00', '6bd40ce1-8869-404b-a883-35a1caf26ae5'),
 ('178', '237', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Rachel Christensen\",\"slug\":\"rachel-christensen\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi! I\\u2019m Rachel. I became a part of Faith Promise in 2003 after my family moved here from Charleston, South Carolina. I\\u2019ve always had a passion for music - but I can\\u2019t think of anything better than using it (along with other creative elements) as a tool to glorify the incredible God we serve. So I started getting in the middle of dramas and worship through the youth group. I kept coming around and ended up interning for several years with the worship ministry.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I officially became a part of the staff the summer of 2009. My official title is \\u201cWorship Resources\\u201d, which means I oversee fpResources along with other odd jobs to help the Worship Ministry function each week. I\\u2019m super excited about what God is doing here and can\\u2019t wait to see how He\\u2019s going to use me to further His kingdom!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\\u2019m currently working on my Bachelors Degree in English (and I feel like I\\u2019ll never finish!) and I LOVE studying abroad. I have a passion for missions and music, and I have no idea what God wants to do with it, but I\\u2019m totally willing to take the path He leads me down. For fun\\u2026 I like to read (I know I\\u2019m a nerd!), play Rock Band (the best game of all time) and I really enjoy quality time of any sort with friends (especially if Starbucks is involved).<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"RachelC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Rachel\",\"19\":\"Worship Resources\",\"17\":\"Christensen\",\"22\":\"1525\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '226b7d00-9d6c-4e55-9bdb-6ddd1bc0db51'),
 ('179', '238', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Natali South\",\"slug\":\"natali-south\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"NataliS@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Natali\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Pastor of Family Ministries\",\"17\":\"South\",\"22\":\"1100\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '2017-09-01 16:42:01', 'b1c8e194-37f1-4e8c-a2fa-eaa8374eabd1'),
 ('180', '239', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Michael Wallace\",\"slug\":\"michael-wallace\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Michael grew up in Greensboro, North Carolina, and graduated from Appalachian State University. Upon graduation, he married his wife, Holly, and they moved to Texas. While in Dallas, Michael earned a Masters in Christian Education from Dallas Theological Seminary and spent five years working with both middle and high school students.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In December of 2009, Michael, Holly and their 2 year old son, Colt, migrated back east to join the Faith Promise staff. Michael and Holly love to spend time hanging out as a family and are eagerly awaiting the birth of their second child this spring!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>While Michael loves all sports, he has a special place in his heart for UNC basketball, Virginia Tech football and the Dallas Cowboys. (He is working desperately to become a Vols fan as well!) In addition to enjoying sports, Michael can usually be found listening to good music or watching a great movie.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>As a side note, if you want to be in his eternal good favor, all it takes is a cold can of Cheerwine. Just in case you were wondering....<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>You can connect with him via <a title=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/michaelbwallace\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/michaelbwallace\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Facebook<\\/a>, <a title=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.twitter.com\\/michaelbwallace\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.twitter.com\\/michaelbwallace\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Twitter<\\/a>, or <a title=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.michaelbwallace.com\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.michaelbwallace.com\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">his blog<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"MichaelW@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Michael\",\"19\":\"High School Pastor\",\"17\":\"Wallace\",\"22\":\"1301\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '955d6fe5-0251-444a-9240-7d5e05754041'),
 ('181', '240', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jason Stubbs\",\"slug\":\"jason-stubbs\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Jason is originally from the beautiful archipelagic country of the Bahamas, where he was born and raised until coming to the US to attend college. Jason is from a strong Christian family that valued faith, education and community service as essential to living out God\\u2019s purpose. In this vein Jason has completed undergraduate studies in Psychology\\/Theology\\/ Music and further graduate seminary studies in Church Ministry\\/Counseling. He is currently pursuing is doctoral studies in leadership and ministry. Jason believes that God has called all believers to live life to its fullest. Jason enjoys worship and is passionate about seeing people connect with God through worship and the Word.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Jason has had ministry experience serving as an assistant vocal director for a major Christian university traveling singing group and worship ministry intern and worship pastor in several ministry settings. While in university Jason met his stunning, godly wife and is eternally grateful for the resplendent beauty that she illuminates not only externally but internally.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Jason enjoys running, go-carts, cricket (a Caribbean sport) and baseball.  Jason is also a social activist and believes that believers also share social responsibility as essential to expressing our Christian care and concern.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Jason has been attending Faith Promise since fall of 2006 and engaged actively in the worship ministry since fall 2007. Jason is a Worship Associate and works with the vocals, and he wants you to be a part of the ministry. He wants you to come ready to have fun while we create, connect and assist in bringing about life change in the lives of people.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Favorite scripture:<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>\\\"For by grace you have been saved through faith; and that not of yourselves, it is the gift of God; not as a result of works, that no one should boast.\\\" Eph. 2:8-9<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"JasonS@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jason\",\"19\":\"Worship Associate - Vocal Director\",\"17\":\"Stubbs\",\"22\":\"1530\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '2017-09-01 16:42:01', '8fc684d2-2581-4273-8fa8-f2bf4c478321'),
 ('182', '242', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gina McClain\",\"slug\":\"gina-mcclain\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Gina is originally from Broken Arrow, Oklahoma. A graduate of the University of Central Oklahoma, she worked in International Banking before God interrupted her career goals. Gina began working for LifeChurch.tv in 1999. Compelled to work with kids and families, Gina found her rhythm in leveraging what happens at church to impact what happens at home.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Gina is driven by the idea of equipping parents for the journey of teaching their kids how to follow Christ. Based upon her experience as a mom, she identifies with the everyday challenges parents wade through. Most of which seem more messy than spiritual. And yet, in the midst of the mess we have the opportunity to demonstrate Jesus to our kids. It\'s the most difficult, challenging &amp; rewarding thing we will ever do.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Gina and Kyle were married in 1994 and have three kids, Keegan Josie &amp; Connor. Following the call to join the Faith Promise family, Kyle and Gina packed up their family in February 2010 and moved to Knoxville.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Gina is a writer, a speaker, a mentor and a coffee snob. If you\'re looking to grease her palm, a double-shot Americano will do the trick.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>You can read more about Gina on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ginamcclain.com\\/\\\">her blog<\\/a>, follow her on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/gina_mcclain\\\">Twitter<\\/a>, or \\\"friend\\\"  on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/gina.mcclain\\\">Facebook<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"GinaM@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"gina.mcclain\",\"16\":\"Gina\",\"25\":\"ginamcclain\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Children\'s Ministries\",\"17\":\"McClain\",\"26\":[\"24\"],\"22\":\"1204\",\"27\":[],\"24\":\"gina_mcclain\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:04', '2017-09-01 16:42:04', '5dab719b-09b0-4031-998b-d6e16488815f'),
 ('183', '243', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Paul McNeill\",\"slug\":\"paul-mcneill\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Paul was born in New York but moved shortly thereafter and was raised in Knoxville, Tennessee.  Paul grew up as a middle child, and accredits \\u201cmiddle child syndrome\\u201d as the cause of his outgoing personality and constant humor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Paul began his call to ministry during high school, working many summers at a Christian camp in Asheville, North Carolina.  He later attended Boyce College at Southern Seminary in Louisville, Kentucky, studying Youth Ministry and Biblical studies, and then returned to Tennessee in 2007 to pursue a degree in Video Production at Pellissippi State.  A year and a half later, he met his beautiful wife Kelly, and the 2 were married in May 2010.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>If he could be any type of animal, Paul would probably be an otter, firstly because they get to experience land and water, and secondly because they always seem to be the animals having the most fun every time he goes to the zoo.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Paul loves anything to do with travel and visiting new places (which probably stems from his dad being a pilot), and has been to all 50 states and over a dozen countries.  He also enjoys movies, music, boats, the mountains, and being around people.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Paul made a living freelance shooting and editing video for commercials, concerts, weddings, and sports before joining the Faith Promise staff in early 2010 as the Student Ministries Program Director.  Paul\\u2019s passion for youth ministry and love of technology drive him to serve God wholeheartedly in his position using the gifts that God has given him.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"PaulM@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Paul\",\"19\":\"Student Ministry Program Director\",\"17\":\"McNeill\",\"22\":\"1302\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:04', '2017-09-01 16:42:04', '6b3c9c01-24d9-438b-929a-db850ff47f9a'),
 ('184', '244', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ashley Caldwell\",\"slug\":\"ashley-caldwell\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"AshleyC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Ashley\",\"19\":\"High School Ministry Assistant\",\"17\":\"Caldwell\",\"22\":\"1300\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:05', '2017-09-01 16:42:05', '64b77190-94b7-4719-a157-cd93293d3d8e'),
 ('185', '245', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Wayne Burress\",\"slug\":\"wayne-burress\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1439933624,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Wayne became the Blount Campus Pastor on March 1st, 2010.  Before joining the staff, he spent almost 20 years designing and developing computer information systems for a couple of Fortune 100 companies.  Regarding his response to God\\u2019s call into full-time ministry, he uses this quote from Andy Stanley \\u201cWhen God invites me, I do what I can do and trust Him to do what only He can do\\u201d.<br \\/>\\nHe and Angie have been married since 1991 and have enjoyed being a part of the Faith Promise family since 2000.  His primary ministry area has been in adult Groups where he\\u2019s served as a group leader and coached new leaders.  In addition, he served as a member of the Leadership Team and volunteered in Children\\u2019s and First Impressions ministries.\\nHe loves to spend time with Angie and their two children, Meredith and Evan.  Sports, reading and time with friends are some of his favorite activities.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"WayneB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Wayne\",\"19\":\"Blount Campus Pastor\",\"17\":\"Burress\",\"22\":\"1706\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:05', '2017-09-01 16:42:05', 'bc564962-610a-4f29-b98d-79b971dddd45'),
 ('186', '246', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Amy McGehee\",\"slug\":\"amy-mcgehee\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"AmyM@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Amy\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Associate Pastor of Groups\",\"17\":\"McGehee\",\"22\":\"1406\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:05', '2017-09-01 16:42:05', 'ad01b690-1d18-46c9-b329-5126c3aae7e4'),
 ('187', '247', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Marcy Dorman\",\"slug\":\"marcy-dorman\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"MarcyD@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Marcy\",\"19\":\"Resource Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Dorman\",\"22\":\"1203\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:05', '2017-09-01 16:42:05', 'ccfafd03-9c25-4ac4-8268-f41b6a548650'),
 ('188', '249', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Aimee Fair\",\"slug\":\"aimee-fair\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1451928903,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"9\"],\"21\":\"AimeeF@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"aimee.g.fair\",\"16\":\"Aimee\",\"25\":\"fairfamilyteam\",\"19\":\"fpKids Preschool Director\",\"17\":\"Fair\",\"26\":[\"24\"],\"27\":[],\"24\":\"AimeeFair1\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 16:42:08', 'f7976bae-2b00-4cf9-af71-04e88fd4e13c'),
 ('189', '250', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Shannan Copland\",\"slug\":\"shannan-copland\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi, I\\u2019m Shannan! I am originally from the SF Bay Area in California, but after high school I joined a touring ministry team based in Knoxville where I met my husband, Nick.  The Lord has kept us here since then and led us to Faith Promise where we are so excited to serve!  I have been at Faith Promise since 2008, the same year Nick and I were married.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>With my music background, I immediately became involved in the Worship Ministry as a volunteer and eventually became a volunteer worship leader.  I was brought on staff in 2010 to fill in as the Assistant to the Worship and Creative Arts Director, which, through a series of events led to a permanent position as the Worship Administrative Assistant.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I am a student at Liberty University Online earning my degree in Biblical Studies with a minor in Christian Counseling.  My husband, Nick, is also a student at Tennessee Temple University Online earning his degree in Biblical Studies with a minor in Intercultural Studies (Missions).  We are so excited to finally be done soon as I will graduate this May of 2011 and he\\u2019ll be done in December, but then it\\u2019s seminary for him!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Interesting Fact:<\\/strong> Four months after Nick and I were married, we headed overseas with the International Mission Board and served in Lisbon, Portugal, for eight months and worked with youth partnering with Young Life International.  We both love traveling and ministry and have big hearts for missions!<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"ShannanC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Shannan\",\"19\":\"Worship Assistant\",\"17\":\"Copland\",\"22\":\"1515\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 16:42:08', 'e83468b9-f3b9-45d6-a42d-032aa83b5463'),
 ('190', '251', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Amber Davis\",\"slug\":\"amber-davis\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1439933624,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I grew up in a home where we put the Lord first. Period. Because my parents were such strong Christian models for me, I became a Christ-follower at a young age and never looked back. I grew up in Knoxville, attended Bearden High School, and then went on to UT to study Journalism and Electronic Media. I started attending Faith Promise in college (2004) and immediately felt drawn to the heart and mission of my new church family-- making it hard to go to hell from East Tennessee.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>After graduating college, I moved to the Tri-Cities to take my first TV reporting job at WJHL. It\'s there that I met and fell head over heels in love with my husband. After my contract was up, I came back in Knoxville. Shawn and I married in 2009, and I was thrilled to bring my husband to Faith Promise, the church where I felt at home.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In 2010, the Lord began to work on my heart. At that point, I had been in TV news for six years (locally, I worked for WATE and WVLT) and that was all I knew of the career world. It had been my dream. But I began to feel uneasy. I knew it wasn\'t my heart\'s desire anymore. That was truly scary for such a control freak like me. It was scary until I heard four words from Executive Pastor Josh Whitehead, \\\"You want a job?\\\" Yes! If there\'s anything else I\'d rather be doing, it\'s serving my God in ministry! And Family Ministry?! That\'s perfect. I know first-hand the difference a strong foundation makes, and I\'d love to dedicate myself to helping others live that abundant life out at home.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>So, that\'s how I went from working in TV to working for Jesus. Let me encourage you to never ignore that still, small voice. He may be calling you to the greatest adventure of your life!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>(If you want to join me without making a huge life change... come serve in fpKiDS! What a joy it is!)<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"AmberD@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Amber\",\"19\":\"fpKids Volunteer Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Davis\",\"22\":\"1201\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 16:42:08', 'edfc00f2-a027-4b0f-b447-046916d8ae65'),
 ('191', '252', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jayson Hines\",\"slug\":\"jayson-hines\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"JaysonH@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jayson\",\"19\":\"Blount Campus Student Ministry Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Hines\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '2017-09-01 16:42:08', '30349e8e-8963-4afc-8186-60c5deca917c'),
 ('192', '253', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Barry Dunford\",\"slug\":\"barry-dunford\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I\'ve been apart of Faith Promise Church since the beginning. I joined the kingdom in 1993, and I started serving in the tech ministry at an early age. At 12, I was running a camera for services, when we met in the mall.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I have bounced around ministries for the past 15 years - from running audio for our kid\'s ministry, doing lights for youth, editing videos for the weekend services, running lights for the weekend services, and designing sets for sermon series. You can say that I have been training for this my whole life. I truly am blessed to work for God and Be able to serve with People that I call my friends and family.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I enjoy playing disc golf and hiking. I also enjoy spending time with my fianc\\u00e9e Ashley. I love all types of music, and I listen to anything from Hillsong, Need To Breath, Sara Groves, and Frank Sinatra.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>It\'s hard for me to choose my favorite movie, but I like all Tim Burton flicks and most dramas. A few of my favorites are Big Fish, A Beautiful Mind, Edward Scissor Hands, and Good Will Hunting.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"BarryD@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Barry\",\"19\":\"Live Production Director\",\"17\":\"Dunford\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:09', '2017-09-01 16:42:09', '28d42756-4fee-4500-b3ac-b63621a5e690'),
 ('193', '255', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Brenda Moore\",\"slug\":\"brenda-moore\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was married to my high school sweetheart for 37 1\\/2 years. My late husband, Terry, and I served in the ministry together for over 30 years. We have four grown sons and five grandchildren (3 boys and 2 girls).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Terry and Pastor Chris were friends and frequently met together. Terry often said, \\\"If we didn\'t have a church of our own, we would be at Faith Promise.\\\" When he was killed in an accident on July 4th of 2009, I realized that I was too distracted to worship at the church my husband and I had started in Clinton, TN. So in the fall of 2009, I began to attend Faith Promise on my own.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I felt God calling me to be a part of Faith Promise\'s staff when I began to feel a restlessness in my spirit at my former job. As I prayed about that restlessness, it became very clear to me that I was to be on staff, but I didn\'t know where God was going to put me. One morning during my quiet time, I felt the restlessness in an even greater way. I asked God, \\\"What are you trying to tell me? Why am I suddenly so discontent where I am?\\\"<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>That very afternoon I got a call from my youngest son who told me he had been on FP\'s website and had found the perfect job for me. I went home, got online, and applied for the Receptionist\'s position. Several interviews and a couple of months later, I received a call that I was being offered the job. I accepted on the spot. I began working at Faith Promise in the fall of 2011. What a blessing it has been to be a part of this team!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I am involved in fpWomen\'s Groups as part of the Leadership Team. I also lead women\'s Bible studies and serve as a baptism assistant.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In my spare time, I love to be with my family-especially with my grandchildren. I also love to read and travel and have a heart for missions.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I am deathly afraid of snakes! I have been known to do a wicked snake dance upon spotting one.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"BrendaM@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"brenda.d.moore.3\",\"16\":\"Brenda\",\"19\":\"Receptionist\",\"17\":\"Moore\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1000\",\"27\":[]}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:12', '2017-09-01 16:42:12', '6f83fdba-c0f1-4810-be07-dff615934551'),
 ('194', '256', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Justine Belk\",\"slug\":\"justine-belk\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hey! My name is Justine. I started coming to Faith Promise in 2006 and attended with my family until I moved to Birmingham, Alabama, for an Internship program with a Church there. After returning to Knoxville in 2011, my love for Faith Promise grew, and I knew that it was a place I wanted to be a part of.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In the fall of 2011 God answered my prayers and blessed me with the opportunity to serve on staff! A few months later, he opened the door for me to become the Apprentice Coordinator of Student Ministries! The title is just a fancy name for helping people put action to the calling that they feel God has given them.  I know that the Lord has incredible plans for this Church, and I fully believe that He is going to use Faith Promise to make it hard to go to hell, not only from East Tennessee, but also from the nations.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>As well as working with our volunteers in fpStudents and helping people get involved here at FPC, I also have a passion for working with young girls to help them realize who they are in Christ. I believe that you don\'t have to be in your twenties or later to find God and truly experience His love.  Because of this passion, I am currently working on my Bachelor\'s in Psychology at the University of Tennessee.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\'m not sure how God is going to use me exactly; all I know is that I am ready and willing to go wherever he leads.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"JustineB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Justine\",\"19\":\"fpStudents Apprenticing Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Belk\",\"22\":\"1006\"}}', '2017-09-01 16:42:12', '2017-09-01 16:42:12', '14363cda-6c58-4a13-b9f7-35baaca695b0'),
