 ('331', '232', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dr. Chuck Carringer\",\"slug\":\"chuck-carringer\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>In my role as Pastor of Leadership Development and Stewardship I partner with staff and volunteers to increase leadership capacity and stewardship across Faith Promise. From 2009-2014 I served as Pastor of Family Ministry. Prior to joining the staff I served for 24 years in public schools. From 1990-2009 I was part of the faculty at Oak Ridge High School serving in a variety of roles including: teacher, coach, vice principal, athletic director, and principal.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My wife Emily, of 25 years, and I have been members of Faith Promise since the church began. I volunteered in a number of ministry areas including serving as an elder, student ministry, school of leaders, and membership classes.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In addition to my role at Faith Promise I provide executive coaching to business leaders. I have a doctorate in executive leadership as well as being a John Maxwell Team Certified Coach, Speaker and Trainer. In addition to executive coaching, I speak frequently to business teams and organizations.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I enjoy family time, and Em, Zach (20 years old), and Maggie (17 years old). We love traveling, especially to the beach! In addition to family fun I enjoy sports, reading, exercising, and time with friends.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Follow Chuck on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/chuckcarringer\\\" target=\\\"blank\\\">Twitter<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/chuckcarringer\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Facebook<\\/a>, or <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.chuckcarringer.com\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">his blog<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"ChuckC@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"chuckcarringer\",\"16\":\"Chuck\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Leadership Development & Stewardship\",\"17\":\"Carringer\",\"26\":[\"22\"],\"22\":\"1101\",\"27\":[\"419\"],\"24\":\"chuckcarringer\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:20', '2017-09-01 18:25:20', '7541d166-3a43-4a38-8f2a-2e3d1afaf11d'),
 ('332', '233', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Melanie Goodman\",\"slug\":\"melanie-goodman\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>We started attending Faith Promise Church in 2007, and I joined the awesome Faith Promise Family Ministry Staff in February 2009.  I am very blessed to be given the opportunity to serve God doing the very thing God has equipped me for!  I am the assistant to the Middle School Pastor and love working with the student ministry staff and students.  I have an overwhelming desire to help teenage students experience a personal relationship with God and help equip them with the tools they need to make good choices that will impact their lives forever.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\'ve been happily married to my husband Jonathan Goodman since January 18, 1992.  I\'m the luckiest lady alive to be married to the love of my life and best friend!!  Along with Jonathan came a special blessing, my step-son Justin who I love very much.  Together Jonathan and I have two children, Zeke and Darah.  We love spending time together as a family.  We camp, ride bikes, run, and love anything that involves a beach.  We have fun doing anything as long as were together.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I was extremely blessed for the privilege and support of my husband to be able to stay home to raise my children for 15 years.  During that time I worked part time as a children\'s ministry director at a previous church and also as a substitute teacher.  I spent numerous hours volunteering and loving every minute I spent being with Zeke and Darah.  I am humbled that God would loan such precious children to me so I could be their mom!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Hobbies:  I love to read anything that helps me to grow spiritually, and my guilty pleasure: Karen Kingsbury novels.  I love to run!  Yes I said it, I love to run!  When I\'ve had a stressful day, running always sets me at ease.  I use this time to meditate on all God has for me - except for the times I\'m begging God to get me through the next mile!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Favorite bible verse: Search me, O God, and know my heart; test me and know my anxious thoughts.  See if there is any offensive way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.  Psalm 139: 23-24<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"MelanieG@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Melanie\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Middle School Pastor\",\"17\":\"Goodman\",\"22\":\"1305\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:20', '2017-09-01 18:25:20', '5695d114-b04b-4a08-9566-0f3c333e636a'),
 ('333', '234', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Deneen Lambert\",\"slug\":\"deneen-lambert\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1442552400,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"DeneenL@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"deneen.lambert\",\"16\":\"Deneen\",\"25\":\"deneenl\",\"19\":\"Finance Assistant\",\"17\":\"Lambert\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1600\",\"24\":\"deneenl14\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:20', '2017-09-01 18:25:20', 'ea1baa0b-1f4b-4fc6-b8d8-ab2ba790e9d6'),
 ('334', '236', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Joe Filipowicz\",\"slug\":\"joe-filipowicz\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was born in Toledo Ohio but moved to Knoxville in 1989.  While I like Tennessee Football I am a die hard Ohio State fan!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My wife Donna and I started dating in high school and have been married for {{ \'1994-10-01\' | age }} awesome years. We have two kids \\u2013 Katie, {{ \'1995-10-01\' | age }} and Brandon, {{ \'1998-09-01\' | age }}.  Katie is a sophomore at the University of Tennessee and Brandon is a Junior in high school. They are both involved with the church and we couldn\\u2019t be prouder of who they have become!!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I have been working at Faith Promise Church for {{ \'2009-09-01\' | age }} years and love coming to work everyday!  I enjoy Basketball, soccer, football and... well pretty much anything that\\u2019s competitive.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"JoeF@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"joe.filipowicz.jr\",\"16\":\"Joe\",\"25\":\"joeflip\",\"19\":\"IT Director\",\"17\":\"Filipowicz\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1605\",\"27\":[\"442\"],\"24\":\"joeflip2\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:25', '2017-09-01 18:25:25', '70f17ce1-af87-45dd-bb53-c7710ac2fcb6'),
 ('335', '237', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Rachel Christensen\",\"slug\":\"rachel-christensen\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi! I\\u2019m Rachel. I became a part of Faith Promise in 2003 after my family moved here from Charleston, South Carolina. I\\u2019ve always had a passion for music - but I can\\u2019t think of anything better than using it (along with other creative elements) as a tool to glorify the incredible God we serve. So I started getting in the middle of dramas and worship through the youth group. I kept coming around and ended up interning for several years with the worship ministry.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I officially became a part of the staff the summer of 2009. My official title is \\u201cWorship Resources\\u201d, which means I oversee fpResources along with other odd jobs to help the Worship Ministry function each week. I\\u2019m super excited about what God is doing here and can\\u2019t wait to see how He\\u2019s going to use me to further His kingdom!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\\u2019m currently working on my Bachelors Degree in English (and I feel like I\\u2019ll never finish!) and I LOVE studying abroad. I have a passion for missions and music, and I have no idea what God wants to do with it, but I\\u2019m totally willing to take the path He leads me down. For fun\\u2026 I like to read (I know I\\u2019m a nerd!), play Rock Band (the best game of all time) and I really enjoy quality time of any sort with friends (especially if Starbucks is involved).<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"RachelC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Rachel\",\"19\":\"Worship Resources\",\"17\":\"Christensen\",\"22\":\"1525\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:25', '2017-09-01 18:25:25', '10807202-8ace-4763-a0b6-2c15f3592c12'),
 ('336', '238', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Natali South\",\"slug\":\"natali-south\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"NataliS@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Natali\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Pastor of Family Ministries\",\"17\":\"South\",\"22\":\"1100\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:26', '2017-09-01 18:25:26', 'c1d49132-de03-4317-99fd-b1ab0c72328a'),
 ('337', '239', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Michael Wallace\",\"slug\":\"michael-wallace\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Michael grew up in Greensboro, North Carolina, and graduated from Appalachian State University. Upon graduation, he married his wife, Holly, and they moved to Texas. While in Dallas, Michael earned a Masters in Christian Education from Dallas Theological Seminary and spent five years working with both middle and high school students.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In December of 2009, Michael, Holly and their 2 year old son, Colt, migrated back east to join the Faith Promise staff. Michael and Holly love to spend time hanging out as a family and are eagerly awaiting the birth of their second child this spring!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>While Michael loves all sports, he has a special place in his heart for UNC basketball, Virginia Tech football and the Dallas Cowboys. (He is working desperately to become a Vols fan as well!) In addition to enjoying sports, Michael can usually be found listening to good music or watching a great movie.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>As a side note, if you want to be in his eternal good favor, all it takes is a cold can of Cheerwine. Just in case you were wondering....<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>You can connect with him via <a title=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/michaelbwallace\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/michaelbwallace\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Facebook<\\/a>, <a title=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.twitter.com\\/michaelbwallace\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.twitter.com\\/michaelbwallace\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Twitter<\\/a>, or <a title=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.michaelbwallace.com\\\" href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.michaelbwallace.com\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">his blog<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"MichaelW@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Michael\",\"19\":\"High School Pastor\",\"17\":\"Wallace\",\"22\":\"1301\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:26', '2017-09-01 18:25:26', '023b9eb3-c4c8-4abc-a2d2-113f24a5d803'),
 ('338', '240', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jason Stubbs\",\"slug\":\"jason-stubbs\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Jason is originally from the beautiful archipelagic country of the Bahamas, where he was born and raised until coming to the US to attend college. Jason is from a strong Christian family that valued faith, education and community service as essential to living out God\\u2019s purpose. In this vein Jason has completed undergraduate studies in Psychology\\/Theology\\/ Music and further graduate seminary studies in Church Ministry\\/Counseling. He is currently pursuing is doctoral studies in leadership and ministry. Jason believes that God has called all believers to live life to its fullest. Jason enjoys worship and is passionate about seeing people connect with God through worship and the Word.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Jason has had ministry experience serving as an assistant vocal director for a major Christian university traveling singing group and worship ministry intern and worship pastor in several ministry settings. While in university Jason met his stunning, godly wife and is eternally grateful for the resplendent beauty that she illuminates not only externally but internally.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Jason enjoys running, go-carts, cricket (a Caribbean sport) and baseball.  Jason is also a social activist and believes that believers also share social responsibility as essential to expressing our Christian care and concern.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Jason has been attending Faith Promise since fall of 2006 and engaged actively in the worship ministry since fall 2007. Jason is a Worship Associate and works with the vocals, and he wants you to be a part of the ministry. He wants you to come ready to have fun while we create, connect and assist in bringing about life change in the lives of people.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Favorite scripture:<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>\\\"For by grace you have been saved through faith; and that not of yourselves, it is the gift of God; not as a result of works, that no one should boast.\\\" Eph. 2:8-9<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"JasonS@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jason\",\"19\":\"Worship Associate - Vocal Director\",\"17\":\"Stubbs\",\"22\":\"1530\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:26', '2017-09-01 18:25:26', '25f37fb7-2201-4cc7-b6ba-49425819df73'),
 ('339', '242', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Gina McClain\",\"slug\":\"gina-mcclain\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Gina is originally from Broken Arrow, Oklahoma. A graduate of the University of Central Oklahoma, she worked in International Banking before God interrupted her career goals. Gina began working for LifeChurch.tv in 1999. Compelled to work with kids and families, Gina found her rhythm in leveraging what happens at church to impact what happens at home.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Gina is driven by the idea of equipping parents for the journey of teaching their kids how to follow Christ. Based upon her experience as a mom, she identifies with the everyday challenges parents wade through. Most of which seem more messy than spiritual. And yet, in the midst of the mess we have the opportunity to demonstrate Jesus to our kids. It\'s the most difficult, challenging &amp; rewarding thing we will ever do.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Gina and Kyle were married in 1994 and have three kids, Keegan Josie &amp; Connor. Following the call to join the Faith Promise family, Kyle and Gina packed up their family in February 2010 and moved to Knoxville.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Gina is a writer, a speaker, a mentor and a coffee snob. If you\'re looking to grease her palm, a double-shot Americano will do the trick.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>You can read more about Gina on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ginamcclain.com\\/\\\">her blog<\\/a>, follow her on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/gina_mcclain\\\">Twitter<\\/a>, or \\\"friend\\\"  on <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.facebook.com\\/gina.mcclain\\\">Facebook<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"GinaM@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"gina.mcclain\",\"16\":\"Gina\",\"25\":\"ginamcclain\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Children\'s Ministries\",\"17\":\"McClain\",\"26\":[\"24\"],\"22\":\"1204\",\"27\":[\"424\"],\"24\":\"gina_mcclain\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:31', '2017-09-01 18:25:31', '8f32b253-2bda-4d63-8056-75bdc3d0726d'),
 ('340', '243', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Paul McNeill\",\"slug\":\"paul-mcneill\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Paul was born in New York but moved shortly thereafter and was raised in Knoxville, Tennessee.  Paul grew up as a middle child, and accredits \\u201cmiddle child syndrome\\u201d as the cause of his outgoing personality and constant humor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Paul began his call to ministry during high school, working many summers at a Christian camp in Asheville, North Carolina.  He later attended Boyce College at Southern Seminary in Louisville, Kentucky, studying Youth Ministry and Biblical studies, and then returned to Tennessee in 2007 to pursue a degree in Video Production at Pellissippi State.  A year and a half later, he met his beautiful wife Kelly, and the 2 were married in May 2010.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>If he could be any type of animal, Paul would probably be an otter, firstly because they get to experience land and water, and secondly because they always seem to be the animals having the most fun every time he goes to the zoo.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Paul loves anything to do with travel and visiting new places (which probably stems from his dad being a pilot), and has been to all 50 states and over a dozen countries.  He also enjoys movies, music, boats, the mountains, and being around people.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Paul made a living freelance shooting and editing video for commercials, concerts, weddings, and sports before joining the Faith Promise staff in early 2010 as the Student Ministries Program Director.  Paul\\u2019s passion for youth ministry and love of technology drive him to serve God wholeheartedly in his position using the gifts that God has given him.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"PaulM@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Paul\",\"19\":\"Student Ministry Program Director\",\"17\":\"McNeill\",\"22\":\"1302\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:31', '2017-09-01 18:25:31', 'a21dfbf1-fa70-4b86-b1f6-602a4b1ae417'),
 ('341', '244', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ashley Caldwell\",\"slug\":\"ashley-caldwell\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"AshleyC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Ashley\",\"19\":\"High School Ministry Assistant\",\"17\":\"Caldwell\",\"22\":\"1300\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:32', '2017-09-01 18:25:32', 'c9999c4a-a345-4060-b619-b15946bd1c05'),
 ('342', '245', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Wayne Burress\",\"slug\":\"wayne-burress\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1439933624,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Wayne became the Blount Campus Pastor on March 1st, 2010.  Before joining the staff, he spent almost 20 years designing and developing computer information systems for a couple of Fortune 100 companies.  Regarding his response to God\\u2019s call into full-time ministry, he uses this quote from Andy Stanley \\u201cWhen God invites me, I do what I can do and trust Him to do what only He can do\\u201d.<br \\/>\\nHe and Angie have been married since 1991 and have enjoyed being a part of the Faith Promise family since 2000.  His primary ministry area has been in adult Groups where he\\u2019s served as a group leader and coached new leaders.  In addition, he served as a member of the Leadership Team and volunteered in Children\\u2019s and First Impressions ministries.\\nHe loves to spend time with Angie and their two children, Meredith and Evan.  Sports, reading and time with friends are some of his favorite activities.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"WayneB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Wayne\",\"19\":\"Blount Campus Pastor\",\"17\":\"Burress\",\"22\":\"1706\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:32', '2017-09-01 18:25:32', 'ccd4d3b4-2459-411b-888d-22c09df70fb8'),
 ('343', '246', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Amy McGehee\",\"slug\":\"amy-mcgehee\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"AmyM@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Amy\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Associate Pastor of Groups\",\"17\":\"McGehee\",\"22\":\"1406\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:33', '2017-09-01 18:25:33', 'f86cdac1-45ae-4a7f-88fc-1654af9410f8'),
 ('344', '247', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Marcy Dorman\",\"slug\":\"marcy-dorman\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"MarcyD@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Marcy\",\"19\":\"Resource Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Dorman\",\"22\":\"1203\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:33', '2017-09-01 18:25:33', '54cc4db9-5363-4643-9968-50b9eed8902b'),
 ('345', '249', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Aimee Fair\",\"slug\":\"aimee-fair\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1451928903,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"9\"],\"21\":\"AimeeF@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"aimee.g.fair\",\"16\":\"Aimee\",\"25\":\"fairfamilyteam\",\"19\":\"fpKids Preschool Director\",\"17\":\"Fair\",\"26\":[\"24\"],\"24\":\"AimeeFair1\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:33', '2017-09-01 18:25:33', 'd026615c-002d-4e43-a117-0d4c1c46b36a'),
 ('346', '250', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Shannan Copland\",\"slug\":\"shannan-copland\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi, I\\u2019m Shannan! I am originally from the SF Bay Area in California, but after high school I joined a touring ministry team based in Knoxville where I met my husband, Nick.  The Lord has kept us here since then and led us to Faith Promise where we are so excited to serve!  I have been at Faith Promise since 2008, the same year Nick and I were married.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>With my music background, I immediately became involved in the Worship Ministry as a volunteer and eventually became a volunteer worship leader.  I was brought on staff in 2010 to fill in as the Assistant to the Worship and Creative Arts Director, which, through a series of events led to a permanent position as the Worship Administrative Assistant.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I am a student at Liberty University Online earning my degree in Biblical Studies with a minor in Christian Counseling.  My husband, Nick, is also a student at Tennessee Temple University Online earning his degree in Biblical Studies with a minor in Intercultural Studies (Missions).  We are so excited to finally be done soon as I will graduate this May of 2011 and he\\u2019ll be done in December, but then it\\u2019s seminary for him!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p><strong>Interesting Fact:<\\/strong> Four months after Nick and I were married, we headed overseas with the International Mission Board and served in Lisbon, Portugal, for eight months and worked with youth partnering with Young Life International.  We both love traveling and ministry and have big hearts for missions!<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"ShannanC@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Shannan\",\"19\":\"Worship Assistant\",\"17\":\"Copland\",\"22\":\"1515\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:34', '2017-09-01 18:25:34', '48d90822-f49d-4119-8950-2858c70794f9'),
 ('347', '251', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Amber Davis\",\"slug\":\"amber-davis\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1439933624,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I grew up in a home where we put the Lord first. Period. Because my parents were such strong Christian models for me, I became a Christ-follower at a young age and never looked back. I grew up in Knoxville, attended Bearden High School, and then went on to UT to study Journalism and Electronic Media. I started attending Faith Promise in college (2004) and immediately felt drawn to the heart and mission of my new church family-- making it hard to go to hell from East Tennessee.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>After graduating college, I moved to the Tri-Cities to take my first TV reporting job at WJHL. It\'s there that I met and fell head over heels in love with my husband. After my contract was up, I came back in Knoxville. Shawn and I married in 2009, and I was thrilled to bring my husband to Faith Promise, the church where I felt at home.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In 2010, the Lord began to work on my heart. At that point, I had been in TV news for six years (locally, I worked for WATE and WVLT) and that was all I knew of the career world. It had been my dream. But I began to feel uneasy. I knew it wasn\'t my heart\'s desire anymore. That was truly scary for such a control freak like me. It was scary until I heard four words from Executive Pastor Josh Whitehead, \\\"You want a job?\\\" Yes! If there\'s anything else I\'d rather be doing, it\'s serving my God in ministry! And Family Ministry?! That\'s perfect. I know first-hand the difference a strong foundation makes, and I\'d love to dedicate myself to helping others live that abundant life out at home.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>So, that\'s how I went from working in TV to working for Jesus. Let me encourage you to never ignore that still, small voice. He may be calling you to the greatest adventure of your life!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>(If you want to join me without making a huge life change... come serve in fpKiDS! What a joy it is!)<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"AmberD@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Amber\",\"19\":\"fpKids Volunteer Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Davis\",\"22\":\"1201\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:34', '2017-09-01 18:25:34', 'abb5c88f-bfeb-4c42-9815-2f32f8b73c3b'),
 ('348', '252', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jayson Hines\",\"slug\":\"jayson-hines\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"JaysonH@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jayson\",\"19\":\"Blount Campus Student Ministry Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Hines\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:35', '2017-09-01 18:25:35', 'd1295487-bc50-4218-aca9-2c6a24d7ddbd'),
 ('349', '253', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Barry Dunford\",\"slug\":\"barry-dunford\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I\'ve been apart of Faith Promise Church since the beginning. I joined the kingdom in 1993, and I started serving in the tech ministry at an early age. At 12, I was running a camera for services, when we met in the mall.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I have bounced around ministries for the past 15 years - from running audio for our kid\'s ministry, doing lights for youth, editing videos for the weekend services, running lights for the weekend services, and designing sets for sermon series. You can say that I have been training for this my whole life. I truly am blessed to work for God and Be able to serve with People that I call my friends and family.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I enjoy playing disc golf and hiking. I also enjoy spending time with my fianc\\u00e9e Ashley. I love all types of music, and I listen to anything from Hillsong, Need To Breath, Sara Groves, and Frank Sinatra.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>It\'s hard for me to choose my favorite movie, but I like all Tim Burton flicks and most dramas. A few of my favorites are Big Fish, A Beautiful Mind, Edward Scissor Hands, and Good Will Hunting.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"BarryD@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Barry\",\"19\":\"Live Production Director\",\"17\":\"Dunford\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:35', '2017-09-01 18:25:35', '5e7793d8-1a5c-4ef3-9876-88b396db2c03'),
 ('350', '255', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Brenda Moore\",\"slug\":\"brenda-moore\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was married to my high school sweetheart for 37 1\\/2 years. My late husband, Terry, and I served in the ministry together for over 30 years. We have four grown sons and five grandchildren (3 boys and 2 girls).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Terry and Pastor Chris were friends and frequently met together. Terry often said, \\\"If we didn\'t have a church of our own, we would be at Faith Promise.\\\" When he was killed in an accident on July 4th of 2009, I realized that I was too distracted to worship at the church my husband and I had started in Clinton, TN. So in the fall of 2009, I began to attend Faith Promise on my own.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I felt God calling me to be a part of Faith Promise\'s staff when I began to feel a restlessness in my spirit at my former job. As I prayed about that restlessness, it became very clear to me that I was to be on staff, but I didn\'t know where God was going to put me. One morning during my quiet time, I felt the restlessness in an even greater way. I asked God, \\\"What are you trying to tell me? Why am I suddenly so discontent where I am?\\\"<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>That very afternoon I got a call from my youngest son who told me he had been on FP\'s website and had found the perfect job for me. I went home, got online, and applied for the Receptionist\'s position. Several interviews and a couple of months later, I received a call that I was being offered the job. I accepted on the spot. I began working at Faith Promise in the fall of 2011. What a blessing it has been to be a part of this team!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I am involved in fpWomen\'s Groups as part of the Leadership Team. I also lead women\'s Bible studies and serve as a baptism assistant.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In my spare time, I love to be with my family-especially with my grandchildren. I also love to read and travel and have a heart for missions.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I am deathly afraid of snakes! I have been known to do a wicked snake dance upon spotting one.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"BrendaM@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"brenda.d.moore.3\",\"16\":\"Brenda\",\"19\":\"Receptionist\",\"17\":\"Moore\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"22\":\"1000\",\"27\":[\"413\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:25:40', '2017-09-01 18:25:40', 'b3c4569e-0478-49cc-9572-01a2e6a6e6d8'),
 ('351', '256', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Justine Belk\",\"slug\":\"justine-belk\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1371826972,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hey! My name is Justine. I started coming to Faith Promise in 2006 and attended with my family until I moved to Birmingham, Alabama, for an Internship program with a Church there. After returning to Knoxville in 2011, my love for Faith Promise grew, and I knew that it was a place I wanted to be a part of.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In the fall of 2011 God answered my prayers and blessed me with the opportunity to serve on staff! A few months later, he opened the door for me to become the Apprentice Coordinator of Student Ministries! The title is just a fancy name for helping people put action to the calling that they feel God has given them.  I know that the Lord has incredible plans for this Church, and I fully believe that He is going to use Faith Promise to make it hard to go to hell, not only from East Tennessee, but also from the nations.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>As well as working with our volunteers in fpStudents and helping people get involved here at FPC, I also have a passion for working with young girls to help them realize who they are in Christ. I believe that you don\'t have to be in your twenties or later to find God and truly experience His love.  Because of this passion, I am currently working on my Bachelor\'s in Psychology at the University of Tennessee.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\'m not sure how God is going to use me exactly; all I know is that I am ready and willing to go wherever he leads.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"JustineB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Justine\",\"19\":\"fpStudents Apprenticing Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Belk\",\"22\":\"1006\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:27:12', '2017-09-01 18:27:12', '6beadd18-fc02-4df1-9fcf-ac4199777360'),
