 ('381', '356', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kandice Baker\",\"slug\":\"kandice-baker\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Kandice grew up in Johnson City, Tennessee, and graduated at the University of Tennessee. While in college, she met and married the love of her life, Mike, who led her to the Lord.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>They were soon after blessed with a baby girl, and their family grew to five kids. Kandice was a stay-at-home mom for many years.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Her experience as a mother of five children allows her to connect with families on a personal level as she relates to everyday life and the challenges of raising kids. Her passion is to connect people to God, to each other, and to service. She especially loves hearing the stories of young people accepting Jesus.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Kandice joined the fpKids staff in 2003 and became the North Knoxville Children\'s Ministry Director in January 2012. Her husband, Mike, serves as the North Knoxville Campus Pastor of Faith Promise.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"11\"],\"21\":\"KandiceB@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"kandice.n.baker\",\"16\":\"Kandice\",\"25\":\"kandimbaker\",\"19\":\"North Knoxville Campus fpKids Director\",\"17\":\"Baker\",\"26\":[\"24\"],\"22\":\"1103\",\"27\":[\"447\"],\"24\":\"Kandice_Baker\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:36:51', '2017-09-01 18:36:51', '21c0518d-bd4d-47d5-ab8c-f4857dd5b7ac'),
 ('382', '358', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tommy Blackburn\",\"slug\":\"tommy-blackburn\",\"postDate\":1457330400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"128\"],\"21\":\"TommyB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Tommy\",\"19\":\"Farragut Campus Student Pastor\",\"17\":\"Blackburn\",\"26\":[\"25\"],\"27\":[\"482\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:36:56', '2017-09-01 18:36:56', '4b2e8bc6-0174-4bc4-9cb2-0d36e64351c9'),
 ('383', '360', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dr. Ann Slimp\",\"slug\":\"ann-slimp\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Ann is a licensed psychologist who integrates her faith in God with her professional skills to minister to people through her role as a counselor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She received her Ph.D. in psychology, at Auburn University in 1991 and has been licensed in TN since 1992.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She has two awesome children - a daughter who is 18 and a son who is 15. They continue to be her greatest teachers.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She has been a Christian since her childhood and continues to be astounded at God\'s abundant grace in her life.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"AnnS@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Ann\",\"19\":\"Staff Counselor\",\"17\":\"Slimp\",\"26\":[\"28\",\"31\"],\"27\":[\"405\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:00', '2017-09-01 18:37:00', '76f089f4-5d30-4444-baca-7cec36fdda7c'),
 ('384', '362', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Penny Spivey\",\"slug\":\"penny-spivey\",\"postDate\":1452010754,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"PennyS@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Penny\",\"19\":\"Next Steps Assistant\",\"17\":\"Spivey\",\"26\":[\"28\",\"30\"],\"27\":[\"468\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:05', '2017-09-01 18:37:05', '43dd8013-f22a-42fc-a7bd-9a5e85244d72'),
 ('385', '364', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kelsey Arnold\",\"slug\":\"kelsey-arnold\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi! My name is Kelsey. My husband and I have been attending Faith Promise for a little over a year now. In April of this year I was granted an amazing opportunity to come on staff as the Assistant to the Pastor of Outreach and Missions. I have always had a passion for serving others and absolutely LOVE what I do. I love to laugh and have a good time.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>When I am not in the office, I enjoy spending time with my friends and family. I also like to spend time outdoors, whether I am kayaking, riding my bike (which I\'m terrible at), or sitting down to read a good book, there\'s nothing better than the warmth of the sun beaming down on my skin.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"KelseyA@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"kelsey.arnold.5\",\"16\":\"Kelsey\",\"19\":\"Missions Assistant\",\"17\":\"Arnold\",\"26\":[\"26\",\"29\"],\"22\":\"1408\",\"27\":[\"448\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:09', '2017-09-01 18:37:09', 'bbcfcf43-ece3-4d82-897d-06060ec52baa'),
 ('386', '366', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Abby Goodman\",\"slug\":\"abby-goodman\",\"postDate\":1450368974,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hello Everyone! My name is Abby Goodman and I have been on staff with Faith Promise since December 2015. I have lived in Knoxville area for about three years now after moving from the Memphis area. I graduated from Collierville High School and now I am working towards my bachelors in Marketing Management at the University of Memphis, where I will graduate in May 2016. In my spare time I love to workout, shop, and spend time with my family.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\\u2019m so excited to be part of Faith Promise! I can\\u2019t wait to see what all God has in store for me here!<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"AbbyG@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Abby\",\"19\":\"Finance Assistant\",\"17\":\"Goodman\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"27\":[\"402\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:14', '2017-09-01 18:37:14', 'd5f01d97-8e87-428e-87d4-bc77ed92654e'),
 ('387', '367', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Holden Baker\",\"slug\":\"holden-baker\",\"postDate\":1472619600,\"expiryDate\":1501218000,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"HoldenB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Holden\",\"19\":\"Student Tech Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Baker\",\"26\":[\"25\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:15', '2017-09-01 18:37:15', 'a66ddd40-e448-4a8d-9f45-70d2ccf59e57'),
 ('388', '369', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kyle Wall\",\"slug\":\"kyle-wall\",\"postDate\":1449586982,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Kyle grew up in south Louisiana and loves cajun food and SEC football. He attended Liberty University where he earned a degree in Religion with a Pastoral Ministry focus. He and his wife of 29 years, Melanie, met on Youth Quest Singers while at Liberty. They have been blessed with two daughters, Emily and Olivia.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>For the past 30 years, Kyle and Melanie have served in churches across the country. Kyle has served as a Student Ministries Pastor, Associate\\/Teaching Pastor and Lead Pastor. His passion is to make disciples who make disciples.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>For fun, Kyle enjoys running, golf, shooting guns and reading. There is always a good chance you might run into him at your local Starbucks or \\nChick-fil-a.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"KyleW@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Kyle\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Groups and Missions\",\"17\":\"Wall\",\"26\":[\"26\",\"29\"],\"27\":[\"458\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:18', '2017-09-01 18:37:18', 'b610ea2b-58cc-4839-8495-49c207275778'),
 ('389', '371', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Rob Patrick\",\"slug\":\"rob-patrick\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Rob is originally from Castlewood, VA, a small town in a rural part of Southwest Virginia. He moved from Virginia to Kansas City in 1984 and then to Knoxville in 1986 for his then current job working in the engineering, testing and exploration industry. Rob served as an upper-level manager in the last half of his 33 years in that field of work. He married Jennifer in July of 1988, and they have two children, Adam (26) and Brittany (22).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Rob grew up in a Christian home and began his Christian walk at twelve years old. He began serving in his church and doing ministry at a very early age. Rob served in a number of leadership and ministry roles in the previous two churches he attended here in Knoxville where he served in their children\'s ministry, worship ministry, and as Chairman of the Leadership Team. He has been attending Faith Promise Church since January 2002. Soon afterward attending for the first time, he and his family attended a small group, which began his love for small group ministry. He started out as a volunteer Leader in Small Group Ministry, became a Groups Coach, then served as Community Pastor. He also served on the church\'s Leadership Team before coming on staff in 2011.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Rob has a passion for people and for them to experience life change. He believes that happens best in circles and not rows. He spent a lot of his life in rows growing up and he now believes he experienced his greatest life change in a group. Rob wants everyone to be able to experience the same life change through groups that he experienced. He believes that group life is where God helped him to really begin to understand the Gospel, and the calling on his life to become a disciple and a disciple maker.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In his free time, he and his wife, Jennifer love to spend time at the lake with friends and family and make frequent visits to the Smoky Mountains. Rob loves fishing, boating, and watching sports. He is a UT Vols, Kansas City Chiefs, and Royals fan.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"RobP@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Rob\",\"19\":\"Pellissippi Pastor of Groups and Missions\",\"17\":\"Patrick\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"22\":\"1005\",\"27\":[\"471\"],\"24\":\"RealRobPatrick\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:22', '2017-09-01 18:37:22', '3a841d8b-33d3-45b3-9134-3452904c56d8'),
 ('390', '522', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Shawn Reece\",\"slug\":\"shawn-reece-1\",\"postDate\":1467176400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"shawnr@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Shawn\",\"19\":\"Filmmaker\",\"17\":\"Reece\",\"26\":[\"27\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:23', '2017-09-01 18:37:23', '73385db1-9f01-4e82-be2c-45d05bd26f38'),
 ('391', '374', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dr. Josh Whitehead\",\"slug\":\"josh-whitehead\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Josh became Executive Pastor at Faith Promise in 2005, after serving as the Young Adult Pastor for almost 2 years. His goal is to lead the church by implementing the vision and values through the staff, campuses and ministries.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Josh\'s educational background includes a degree in Business Administration from Louisiana State University, a Masters of Divinity degree from Southwestern Seminary and a Doctorate in leadership and administration. He married his wife Kim in 2002 and they have 2 children \\u2013 Hayden and Madison.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"JoshW@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Josh\",\"25\":\"joshuawhitehead\",\"19\":\"Executive Pastor\",\"17\":\"Whitehead\",\"26\":[\"22\"],\"22\":\"1701\",\"27\":[\"445\"],\"24\":\"joshuawhitehead\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:27', '2017-09-01 18:37:27', '0a5eb607-5744-4e1d-bca2-2ed3f253ab52'),
 ('392', '376', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A.J. Rucker\",\"slug\":\"aj-rucker\",\"postDate\":1472619600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"ajr@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"A.J.\",\"19\":\"Student Experience Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Rucker\",\"26\":[\"25\"],\"27\":[\"410\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:31', '2017-09-01 18:37:31', 'b769476b-62f6-4e84-9fcd-a4abbdc7b1f2'),
 ('393', '378', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jody Kenyon\",\"slug\":\"jody-kenyon\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Jody and her family have been at Faith Promise since the beginning of the church, and she came on staff in February 2001.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Her favorite food is seafood, least favorite food is peas, and greatest fear is snakes.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She has two children, Brandon and Brianna and two beautiful grandchildren, Greyson and Saylor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Favorite hobbies:\\nSpending time with her family and traveling anywhere warm and coastal!<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"JodyK@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"jody.kenyon.9404\",\"16\":\"Jody\",\"25\":\"jodykenyon\",\"19\":\"Executive Assistant to Pastor of Groups and Missions\",\"17\":\"Kenyon\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"22\":\"1400\",\"27\":[\"440\"],\"24\":\"jodykenyon\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:35', '2017-09-01 18:37:35', '40e0746d-4e20-4246-ac77-7843439a46eb'),
 ('394', '379', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Sonja Moore\",\"slug\":\"sonja-moore\",\"postDate\":1467176400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"13\"],\"21\":\"sonjam@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Sonja\",\"19\":\"Anderson Campus Producer\",\"17\":\"Moore\",\"26\":[\"27\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:36', '2017-09-01 18:37:36', '329f5242-4a56-471d-8fa1-ed8752b05640'),
 ('395', '381', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Heidi Reed\",\"slug\":\"heidi-reed\",\"postDate\":1473656400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"11\"],\"21\":\"heidir@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Heidi\",\"19\":\"North Knox fpKids Administrative Assistant\",\"17\":\"Reed\",\"26\":[\"24\"],\"27\":[\"427\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:41', '2017-09-01 18:37:41', 'e97652b5-bbb4-43b0-8155-b08dda1afbb0'),
 ('396', '383', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jessica Elston\",\"slug\":\"jessica-elston\",\"postDate\":1461906000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I grew up in Talladega, Alabama (Yes, like Talladega Nights). After graduating high school I attended Berea College in Kentucky, where I played basketball for three years, and received a BA in Physical Education. In 2012, I went on a Summer Project with CRU (campus crusades college ministry) where I lived in Gatlinburg, TN for the summer. It was there, that I felt called into ministry. God affirmed my gifts in worship, and I began leading in a local church when I returned back to Berea for my senior year.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>After graduating college, I moved home to Alabama and attended Church of the Highlands ministry school, Highlands College in Birmingham. There, I was able to develop my gifts, as well as be discipled by incredible leaders. There, I fell in love with the local church, and grew an even deeper passion for leading people into God\'s presence through worship. After graduating Highlands College, I moved to Knoxville to intern with Faith Promise. It felt like home right away. I am so excited to join this team and continue to see God\'s hand on Faith Promise Church, and to see East Tennessee come to know Christ, and find freedom!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>One more thing, I\'m a HUGE Auburn fan. WAR EAGLE!<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"jessicae@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jessica\",\"19\":\"Worship Associate - Infuse Administration\",\"17\":\"Elston\",\"26\":[\"27\"],\"27\":[\"439\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:45', '2017-09-01 18:37:45', '35b21c1c-85f7-4531-a595-d41ad76e2c27'),
 ('397', '385', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Logan Hankins\",\"slug\":\"logan-hankins\",\"postDate\":1472619600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"LoganH@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Logan\",\"19\":\"Student Creative Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Hankin\",\"26\":[\"25\"],\"27\":[\"454\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:49', '2017-09-01 18:37:49', '4ad3e635-1319-4c73-98ac-151fccd0aa7e'),
 ('398', '387', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Lance Asher\",\"slug\":\"lance-asher\",\"postDate\":1444769899,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I have grown up here in beautiful Knoxville, Tennessee my whole life. I grew up in church and have always been active in serving in some capacity, even when I was young. I accepted Christ when I was nine, and shortly after that decision, I lost my father to cancer. I truly believe that God has a sovereign plan for our lives and even through that hurt and pain I was able to learn and grow and trust God wholly and fully. I have been a member at Faith Promise Church since February, 2015 and I have a strong desire to see God\\u2019s love spread throughout this wonderful city.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Music is my passion. I believe that God created art and he gives us creativity and so naturally I appreciate art and creativity myself. Muse is my favorite band and has been since I was a freshman in high school. Fun Fact: I saw them live for my sixteenth birthday and cried. Real tears. As much as I love music though, I grew up first loving sports. Tennis and basketball are my two favorite sports. Novak Djokovic is my favorite tennis player and my favorite basketball team is THE UNIVERSITY OF KENTUCKY. If you\\u2019ll notice, my top player and team are both the best. Before you call me a bandwagon fan, I had pictures of Djokovic on my Myspace page and both sides of my family are die-hard Kentucky fans. Go cats!<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"LanceA@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"lance.asher.9\",\"16\":\"Lance\",\"25\":\"lancejasher\",\"19\":\"Worship Associate - Next Generation Band\",\"17\":\"Asher\",\"26\":[\"27\"],\"27\":[\"451\"],\"24\":\"LanceJAsher\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:54', '2017-09-01 18:37:54', '8674e163-b2d4-4509-ba19-10952164635d'),
 ('399', '389', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Hannah Little\",\"slug\":\"hannah-little\",\"postDate\":1478235600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"HannahL@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Hannah\",\"19\":\"Student Associate\",\"17\":\"Little\",\"26\":[\"25\"],\"27\":[\"426\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:37:59', '2017-09-01 18:37:59', 'ac583e27-36c2-45b5-8147-d34824623e27'),
 ('400', '391', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Justin Petrowski\",\"slug\":\"justin-petrowski\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I\'ve been a follower of Christ since 1987 and can say with confidence that it\'s the best decision I\'ve ever made. I have been a member of Faith Promise Church since its inception in 1995. I have always enjoyed serving here - so when the opportunity arose to serve here full-time I took it! I have been on staff at Faith Promise since 2001 as an intern in the Worship Ministry and have served on full-time staff since 2003. Since then I\'ve had the unique privilege of ministering to thousands of my brothers and sisters each week through my gift of music. I attended Oak Ridge High School in Oak Ridge, TN and graduated there in 1999. I attended the University of Tennessee after that and graduated in 2003 with an honors degree in mathematics. I have been married to my beautiful wife Kara since October 2006.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I love to read, watch and play sports, and make music. I enjoy spending time with my wife and with friends. As far as music goes, I love it all...you\'ll find me listening to anything from Coltrane to Coldplay, Sigur Ros to Sergei Rachmaninoff, U2 to the David Crowder Band and Hillsong. I\'m always into something different. I love to read as well and I love exploring the Bible through fresh sets of eyes. Some of my favorite books include Velvet Elvis by Rob Bell, Blue Like Jazz by Donald Miller, and A Generous Orthodoxy by Brian McLaren. Check them out! I\'m also a HUGE fan of the Green Bay Packers, the Boston Red Sox, NASCAR, and University of Tennessee athletics. Go VOLS!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>God bless you!\\nHebrews 12:1-3<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"JustinP@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"justin.lee.petrowski\",\"16\":\"Justin\",\"25\":\"petrowski7\",\"19\":\"Band Director\",\"17\":\"Petrowski\",\"26\":[\"27\"],\"22\":\"1502\",\"27\":[\"444\"],\"24\":\"petrowski7\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:02', '2017-09-01 18:38:02', 'da6bc6ae-1180-4149-b32c-07bbac9e6531'),
 ('401', '393', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jennifer Rose\",\"slug\":\"jennifer-rose\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1476853200,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"JenniferR@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"jennifer.rose.94\",\"16\":\"Jennifer\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Pastor of Leadership Development & Stewardship\",\"17\":\"Rose\",\"22\":\"1100\",\"24\":\"jrose1001\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:02', '2017-09-01 18:38:02', '01a90a1e-1c88-430e-9f14-e906981e1988'),
 ('402', '395', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Martha Williams\",\"slug\":\"martha-williams\",\"postDate\":1477285200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi.  My name is Martha Williams.  I moved to the Knoxville area in 2013 from Washington State to be with my daughter and her family.  After losing several family members to cancer, including my parents and husband, it was time for a change and to be close to my 4 grandchildren (2 girls and 2 boys). Moving to Knoxville meant that I left behind my son and his then new bride.  Now, I\'m missing their first daughter and a second daughter due January, 2017.  It just means I get to go back and visit them as often as I can!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>When I would visit Knoxville, I would always attend Faith Promise with my family.  There was no question where I was going to attend church once I moved here.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>After my husband\'s death in 2005, I took over the operation of his business, a produce brokerage. Prior to that I had been a CPA, working in private accounting, industry and government.  In the beginning of 2016 I entered into semi-retirement. I had been praying and asking God what this next season would look like.  I felt God telling me to trust Him, that he had something good planned.  I had been volunteering in the Finance office when I was asked if I would take a temporary position, filling in for someone on medical leave.  That led to my position as HR Administrator.  I am so honored to work with such a great team of people, furthering the vision and mission of saving souls in East Tennessee.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I love to travel, whether to visit family or exploring and trying new things.  My favorite places to go are Moloka\\u2019i, Hawaii and the San Juan Islands in Washington State.  Anything that involves being on or in the water \\u2013 swimming, boating or scuba diving.  In 2010 I got my open water scuba diving certification and my advanced open water in 2014.  Now I try to mix my travels with scuba diving.  When home I enjoy working in the yard, quilting, knitting and spending time with family and my dear sisters in my small groups.  I look forward to what God has planned for this next stage in life.  He is faithful and \\\"I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me\\u201d Phil 4:13.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"marthaw@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Martha\",\"19\":\"HR Administrator\",\"17\":\"Williams\",\"26\":[\"28\",\"28\"],\"27\":[\"460\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:08', '2017-09-01 18:38:08', '02de120e-8319-4c80-b01d-c41159693643'),
 ('403', '397', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kelly Carringer\",\"slug\":\"kelly-carringer\",\"postDate\":1476853200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was born and raised in Knoxville, TN. I\\u2019m the youngest of 7 and have a twin. Growing up in a big family is a huge blessing! I\\u2019ve learned so much from watching other people, and God has taught me so much from my family.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\\u2019ve been attending Faith Promise since August 2010, and I\\u2019m truly blown away by the impact it\\u2019s had on my life. I\\u2019m thrilled to join my husband and the rest of the team on staff! Small groups have grown my walk tremendously and fostered lifelong friendships. I can\\u2019t wait to help other people find the perfect group for their season of life.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Outside of work, I love to travel! You might also find me baking, watching movies, and loving anything Disney.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"kellyc@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Kelly\",\"19\":\"Pellissippi Groups Administrative Assistant\",\"17\":\"Carringer\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"27\":[\"446\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:12', '2017-09-01 18:38:12', '90d56b68-8ebd-464d-ba5c-c100922f98ad'),
 ('404', '399', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Miles Creasman\",\"slug\":\"miles-creasman\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Miles Creasman has been on staff as the Blount Campus Groups Director since June 2010 and also took on the role of Pastor of Next Steps in the middle of 2011. Originally from Riceville, TN, Miles is a graduate of Carson-Newman College and Southern Baptist Theological Seminary in Louisville, KY. He has been in ministry for 15 years and has served on church staffs as Recreation Minister, Middle &amp; High School Pastor, and Singles Pastor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Miles has a passion to help people grow in their relationship with the Lord, and he believes that the context of community found in groups is the best place for that to happen.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Miles has been married to Katy for 13 years, and they have 3 children - Jess (9), Will (7), and Leah (3).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Miles\' favorite hobby is playing with his kids. He loves playing Frisbee golf &amp; fantasy sports. Miles and Katy are both very big UT Vols fans and love to go to games whenever they can.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"9\"],\"21\":\"MilesC@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"miles.creasman\",\"16\":\"Miles\",\"25\":\"bigorange999\",\"19\":\"Blount Campus Pastor of Groups & Missions\",\"17\":\"Creasman\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"22\":\"1005\",\"27\":[\"467\"],\"24\":\"Bigorange99\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:15', '2017-09-01 18:38:15', '2aa0c4b8-7ebd-4000-9931-de5fb9eacdc4'),
 ('405', '536', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Robbie Freeman\",\"slug\":\"robbie-freeman\",\"postDate\":1473656400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was born in Virginia Beach, but my dad\\u2019s career in the Navy took us all over the world. We lived in California, Washington, Mississippi, Ohio, Virginia, Washington D.C., and lived in Scotland for five years.  I began my walk with Christ when I was thirteen-years-old, but joining Faith Promise in 2012 revitalized my faith. My wife Cher and I have been married for many moons and have two rambunctious boys - Ryder and Eli. Cher also has two additional furry children. They are her Yorkie, Aristotle, and Meiko. We love spending time outdoors hiking and stand-up paddle boarding, and playing soccer.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I earned my Bachelor\\u2019s Degree from the University of Memphis in Communications, and I am currently working on a Master\\u2019s Degree in Christian Apologetics at Liberty University. I was a Small Group leader, and coach at the Pellissippi campus for several years and joined the Anderson County campus in August of 2016 as Small Groups Pastor.  I spent fifteen years in restaurant management and currently am a General Manager for Gordon Food Services.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My ministry goal is to glorify God through transformed lives, and I think that small groups are the perfect ministry for that purpose. The Bible passage that I focus my life on is Colossians 1:28-29.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"13\"],\"21\":\"robbief@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Robbie\",\"19\":\"Anderson Campus Pastor of Groups & Missions\",\"17\":\"Freeman\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"27\":[\"474\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:19', '2017-09-01 18:38:19', 'be85c2d5-f6fd-4a71-bf06-0116c169bff2'),
 ('406', '537', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Briauna Gooden\",\"slug\":\"briauna-gooden\",\"postDate\":1478235600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"briaunag@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Briauna\",\"19\":\"Worship Associate\",\"17\":\"Gooden\",\"26\":[\"27\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:20', '2017-09-01 18:38:20', 'f11e774b-df40-470a-8935-c9658c212b7f'),
 ('407', '539', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Wes Selecman\",\"slug\":\"wes-selecman\",\"postDate\":1476853200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"11\"],\"21\":\"wess@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Wes\",\"19\":\"North Knox Groups & Missions Pastor\",\"17\":\"Selecman\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"27\":[\"486\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:24', '2017-09-01 18:38:24', '741e669b-5f8c-4816-9bb4-a63f392947d0'),
 ('408', '540', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Will Hodge\",\"slug\":\"will-hodge\",\"postDate\":1478235600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"15\"],\"21\":\"willh@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Will\",\"19\":\"Campbell Campus Student Pastor\",\"17\":\"Hodge\",\"26\":[\"25\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:24', '2017-09-01 18:38:24', 'f1a0b893-96fd-44c9-a8bb-9311c73e7c5f'),
 ('409', '542', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tony Giordano\",\"slug\":\"tony-giordano\",\"postDate\":1443544970,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hey!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I moved to Tennessee from Florida in August 2014 and have loved it here ever since. The 24\\/7 year round heat of Florida got tiresome after 15 years, so I needed a change! My fianc\\u00e9 (Kate) and I first attended Faith Promise on Easter of 2014, and we fell in love with the Church instantly. I received my B.A.S. Degree in Technology Management in December of 2015, and married my beautiful wife in May of 2016!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>When I was growing up I was a video game enthusiast, which is what got me interested in computers. I still enjoy playing video games occasionally, but I am mainly a technology geek now. I love building computers, researching computer components, and looking at new technologies in my free time. I also enjoy reading, and watching Ice Hockey in my spare time as well. Go <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/lightning.nhl.com\\/club\\/index.htm\\\">Lightning<\\/a>!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I know God meant for me to move to Tennessee because I would have never had an opportunity like this in Florida. I am so thankful for all the staff at Faith Promise for making this church feel like a family, and I am extremely happy to be able to call it my home church.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"TonyG@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"tony.giordano.5458\",\"16\":\"Tony\",\"19\":\"IT Associate\",\"17\":\"Giordano\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"27\":[\"483\"],\"24\":\"Tgiordano92\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:28', '2017-09-01 18:38:28', '22cba13f-4ca3-4d3d-9421-dd9006559119'),
 ('410', '543', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Sara Fulton\",\"slug\":\"sara-fulton\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1480399200,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>My name is Sara Fulton, and my family and I have been attending Faith Promise since 2011. I am originally from Atlanta, GA, and I have been living in Knoxville since 2003 when I moved here for college.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I have had a passion for counseling and reaching out to others since I was a child. I graduated with my Bachelor\'s from Johnson University and my Master\'s from Argosy University. I am hoping to obtain my license in professional counseling in the next few years and will one day return to school to obtain my Ph.D. My goal is to gain all that I can in order to best serve those that I work with. My desire is to love God and to serve others to His glory and purpose.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My husband and I have been married for five years and we have a beautiful daughter who is almost two. We have three crazy dogs and love animals. We love to be outdoors and spending time with family and friends.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"SaraF@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Sara\",\"19\":\"Staff Counselor\",\"17\":\"Fulton\",\"26\":[\"28\",\"31\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:38:28', '2017-09-01 18:38:28', '4486c238-57e7-46df-91ad-614727088dd6'),
 ('411', '356', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kandice Baker\",\"slug\":\"kandice-baker\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Kandice grew up in Johnson City, Tennessee, and graduated at the University of Tennessee. While in college, she met and married the love of her life, Mike, who led her to the Lord.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>They were soon after blessed with a baby girl, and their family grew to five kids. Kandice was a stay-at-home mom for many years.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Her experience as a mother of five children allows her to connect with families on a personal level as she relates to everyday life and the challenges of raising kids. Her passion is to connect people to God, to each other, and to service. She especially loves hearing the stories of young people accepting Jesus.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Kandice joined the fpKids staff in 2003 and became the North Knoxville Children\'s Ministry Director in January 2012. Her husband, Mike, serves as the North Knoxville Campus Pastor of Faith Promise.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"11\"],\"21\":\"KandiceB@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"kandice.n.baker\",\"16\":\"Kandice\",\"25\":\"kandimbaker\",\"19\":\"North Knoxville Campus fpKids Director\",\"17\":\"Baker\",\"26\":[\"24\"],\"22\":\"1103\",\"27\":[\"447\"],\"24\":\"Kandice_Baker\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:39:42', '2017-09-01 18:39:42', '2e1cc7be-e29f-4603-af6b-ea8a74a23b7c'),
 ('412', '358', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tommy Blackburn\",\"slug\":\"tommy-blackburn\",\"postDate\":1457330400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"128\"],\"21\":\"TommyB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Tommy\",\"19\":\"Farragut Campus Student Pastor\",\"17\":\"Blackburn\",\"26\":[\"25\"],\"27\":[\"482\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:39:48', '2017-09-01 18:39:48', '55afc930-9ace-45b7-b72a-0c7d80104953'),
 ('413', '360', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dr. Ann Slimp\",\"slug\":\"ann-slimp\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Ann is a licensed psychologist who integrates her faith in God with her professional skills to minister to people through her role as a counselor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She received her Ph.D. in psychology, at Auburn University in 1991 and has been licensed in TN since 1992.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She has two awesome children - a daughter who is 18 and a son who is 15. They continue to be her greatest teachers.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She has been a Christian since her childhood and continues to be astounded at God\'s abundant grace in her life.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"AnnS@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Ann\",\"19\":\"Staff Counselor\",\"17\":\"Slimp\",\"26\":[\"28\",\"31\"],\"27\":[\"405\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:39:53', '2017-09-01 18:39:53', '305ee24b-a3b0-4e3e-a6d4-34b0b75eef79'),
 ('414', '362', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Penny Spivey\",\"slug\":\"penny-spivey\",\"postDate\":1452010754,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"PennyS@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Penny\",\"19\":\"Next Steps Assistant\",\"17\":\"Spivey\",\"26\":[\"28\",\"30\"],\"27\":[\"468\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:39:56', '2017-09-01 18:39:56', '5c403525-127d-4012-86c8-60bcf65bd6a7'),
 ('415', '364', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kelsey Arnold\",\"slug\":\"kelsey-arnold\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi! My name is Kelsey. My husband and I have been attending Faith Promise for a little over a year now. In April of this year I was granted an amazing opportunity to come on staff as the Assistant to the Pastor of Outreach and Missions. I have always had a passion for serving others and absolutely LOVE what I do. I love to laugh and have a good time.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>When I am not in the office, I enjoy spending time with my friends and family. I also like to spend time outdoors, whether I am kayaking, riding my bike (which I\'m terrible at), or sitting down to read a good book, there\'s nothing better than the warmth of the sun beaming down on my skin.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"KelseyA@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"kelsey.arnold.5\",\"16\":\"Kelsey\",\"19\":\"Missions Assistant\",\"17\":\"Arnold\",\"26\":[\"26\",\"29\"],\"22\":\"1408\",\"27\":[\"448\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:01', '2017-09-01 18:40:01', '5cb7c7ed-007d-4910-94a1-9bdb3a543a68'),
 ('416', '366', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Abby Goodman\",\"slug\":\"abby-goodman\",\"postDate\":1450368974,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hello Everyone! My name is Abby Goodman and I have been on staff with Faith Promise since December 2015. I have lived in Knoxville area for about three years now after moving from the Memphis area. I graduated from Collierville High School and now I am working towards my bachelors in Marketing Management at the University of Memphis, where I will graduate in May 2016. In my spare time I love to workout, shop, and spend time with my family.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\\u2019m so excited to be part of Faith Promise! I can\\u2019t wait to see what all God has in store for me here!<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"AbbyG@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Abby\",\"19\":\"Finance Assistant\",\"17\":\"Goodman\",\"26\":[\"28\"],\"27\":[\"402\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:05', '2017-09-01 18:40:05', 'd7e1d435-c1f9-437f-9449-0bbc4726575e'),
 ('417', '367', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Holden Baker\",\"slug\":\"holden-baker\",\"postDate\":1472619600,\"expiryDate\":1501218000,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"HoldenB@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Holden\",\"19\":\"Student Tech Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Baker\",\"26\":[\"25\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:05', '2017-09-01 18:40:05', 'da87c055-0ef3-4ff9-a8b0-376db3e5a691'),
 ('418', '369', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kyle Wall\",\"slug\":\"kyle-wall\",\"postDate\":1449586982,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Kyle grew up in south Louisiana and loves cajun food and SEC football. He attended Liberty University where he earned a degree in Religion with a Pastoral Ministry focus. He and his wife of 29 years, Melanie, met on Youth Quest Singers while at Liberty. They have been blessed with two daughters, Emily and Olivia.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>For the past 30 years, Kyle and Melanie have served in churches across the country. Kyle has served as a Student Ministries Pastor, Associate\\/Teaching Pastor and Lead Pastor. His passion is to make disciples who make disciples.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>For fun, Kyle enjoys running, golf, shooting guns and reading. There is always a good chance you might run into him at your local Starbucks or \\nChick-fil-a.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"KyleW@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Kyle\",\"19\":\"Pastor of Groups and Missions\",\"17\":\"Wall\",\"26\":[\"26\",\"29\"],\"27\":[\"458\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:10', '2017-09-01 18:40:10', '35b3d1d2-a0ea-41ec-83a9-b1bdf9b97da3'),
 ('419', '371', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Rob Patrick\",\"slug\":\"rob-patrick\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Rob is originally from Castlewood, VA, a small town in a rural part of Southwest Virginia. He moved from Virginia to Kansas City in 1984 and then to Knoxville in 1986 for his then current job working in the engineering, testing and exploration industry. Rob served as an upper-level manager in the last half of his 33 years in that field of work. He married Jennifer in July of 1988, and they have two children, Adam (26) and Brittany (22).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Rob grew up in a Christian home and began his Christian walk at twelve years old. He began serving in his church and doing ministry at a very early age. Rob served in a number of leadership and ministry roles in the previous two churches he attended here in Knoxville where he served in their children\'s ministry, worship ministry, and as Chairman of the Leadership Team. He has been attending Faith Promise Church since January 2002. Soon afterward attending for the first time, he and his family attended a small group, which began his love for small group ministry. He started out as a volunteer Leader in Small Group Ministry, became a Groups Coach, then served as Community Pastor. He also served on the church\'s Leadership Team before coming on staff in 2011.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Rob has a passion for people and for them to experience life change. He believes that happens best in circles and not rows. He spent a lot of his life in rows growing up and he now believes he experienced his greatest life change in a group. Rob wants everyone to be able to experience the same life change through groups that he experienced. He believes that group life is where God helped him to really begin to understand the Gospel, and the calling on his life to become a disciple and a disciple maker.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>In his free time, he and his wife, Jennifer love to spend time at the lake with friends and family and make frequent visits to the Smoky Mountains. Rob loves fishing, boating, and watching sports. He is a UT Vols, Kansas City Chiefs, and Royals fan.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"RobP@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Rob\",\"19\":\"Pellissippi Pastor of Groups and Missions\",\"17\":\"Patrick\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"22\":\"1005\",\"27\":[\"471\"],\"24\":\"RealRobPatrick\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:14', '2017-09-01 18:40:14', 'c34347f9-a848-4b5d-9730-8a3d126c3271'),
 ('420', '552', '3', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Shawn Reece\",\"slug\":\"shawn-reece-2\",\"postDate\":1467176400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"shawnr@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Shawn\",\"19\":\"Filmmaker\",\"17\":\"Reece\",\"26\":[\"27\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:15', '2017-09-01 18:40:15', 'db24dddb-e69c-4298-ae4d-718a024f6790'),
 ('421', '374', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Dr. Josh Whitehead\",\"slug\":\"josh-whitehead\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Josh became Executive Pastor at Faith Promise in 2005, after serving as the Young Adult Pastor for almost 2 years. His goal is to lead the church by implementing the vision and values through the staff, campuses and ministries.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Josh\'s educational background includes a degree in Business Administration from Louisiana State University, a Masters of Divinity degree from Southwestern Seminary and a Doctorate in leadership and administration. He married his wife Kim in 2002 and they have 2 children \\u2013 Hayden and Madison.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"JoshW@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Josh\",\"25\":\"joshuawhitehead\",\"19\":\"Executive Pastor\",\"17\":\"Whitehead\",\"26\":[\"22\"],\"22\":\"1701\",\"27\":[\"445\"],\"24\":\"joshuawhitehead\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:19', '2017-09-01 18:40:19', 'e9655b67-1bd6-43ee-977d-2596c327e613'),
 ('422', '376', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A.J. Rucker\",\"slug\":\"aj-rucker\",\"postDate\":1472619600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"ajr@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"A.J.\",\"19\":\"Student Experience Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Rucker\",\"26\":[\"25\"],\"27\":[\"410\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:23', '2017-09-01 18:40:23', '3e21c16f-75a5-4abe-bd33-907eaa9fc600'),
 ('423', '378', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jody Kenyon\",\"slug\":\"jody-kenyon\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Jody and her family have been at Faith Promise since the beginning of the church, and she came on staff in February 2001.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Her favorite food is seafood, least favorite food is peas, and greatest fear is snakes.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>She has two children, Brandon and Brianna and two beautiful grandchildren, Greyson and Saylor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Favorite hobbies:\\nSpending time with her family and traveling anywhere warm and coastal!<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"JodyK@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"jody.kenyon.9404\",\"16\":\"Jody\",\"25\":\"jodykenyon\",\"19\":\"Executive Assistant to Pastor of Groups and Missions\",\"17\":\"Kenyon\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"22\":\"1400\",\"27\":[\"440\"],\"24\":\"jodykenyon\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:27', '2017-09-01 18:40:27', '2aad588a-4da5-49e6-9bb4-2dfa04e41aea'),
 ('424', '379', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Sonja Moore\",\"slug\":\"sonja-moore\",\"postDate\":1467176400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"13\"],\"21\":\"sonjam@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Sonja\",\"19\":\"Anderson Campus Producer\",\"17\":\"Moore\",\"26\":[\"27\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:28', '2017-09-01 18:40:28', 'cc54b36a-58e5-470c-ba99-35697ebc5eec'),
 ('425', '381', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Heidi Reed\",\"slug\":\"heidi-reed\",\"postDate\":1473656400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"14\":[\"11\"],\"21\":\"heidir@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Heidi\",\"19\":\"North Knox fpKids Administrative Assistant\",\"17\":\"Reed\",\"26\":[\"24\"],\"27\":[\"427\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:32', '2017-09-01 18:40:32', '3caa9f11-a632-478e-b40f-97acb361edec'),
 ('426', '383', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jessica Elston\",\"slug\":\"jessica-elston\",\"postDate\":1461906000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I grew up in Talladega, Alabama (Yes, like Talladega Nights). After graduating high school I attended Berea College in Kentucky, where I played basketball for three years, and received a BA in Physical Education. In 2012, I went on a Summer Project with CRU (campus crusades college ministry) where I lived in Gatlinburg, TN for the summer. It was there, that I felt called into ministry. God affirmed my gifts in worship, and I began leading in a local church when I returned back to Berea for my senior year.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>After graduating college, I moved home to Alabama and attended Church of the Highlands ministry school, Highlands College in Birmingham. There, I was able to develop my gifts, as well as be discipled by incredible leaders. There, I fell in love with the local church, and grew an even deeper passion for leading people into God\'s presence through worship. After graduating Highlands College, I moved to Knoxville to intern with Faith Promise. It felt like home right away. I am so excited to join this team and continue to see God\'s hand on Faith Promise Church, and to see East Tennessee come to know Christ, and find freedom!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>One more thing, I\'m a HUGE Auburn fan. WAR EAGLE!<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"jessicae@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Jessica\",\"19\":\"Worship Associate - Infuse Administration\",\"17\":\"Elston\",\"26\":[\"27\"],\"27\":[\"439\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:37', '2017-09-01 18:40:37', '5fb2aa4b-4d90-4eff-bd98-9cda68c3b7c6'),
 ('427', '385', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Logan Hankins\",\"slug\":\"logan-hankins\",\"postDate\":1472619600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"LoganH@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Logan\",\"19\":\"Student Creative Coordinator\",\"17\":\"Hankin\",\"26\":[\"25\"],\"27\":[\"454\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:42', '2017-09-01 18:40:42', 'd3cb3660-3782-42a6-8b0f-ee600cc1eba9'),
 ('428', '387', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Lance Asher\",\"slug\":\"lance-asher\",\"postDate\":1444769899,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I have grown up here in beautiful Knoxville, Tennessee my whole life. I grew up in church and have always been active in serving in some capacity, even when I was young. I accepted Christ when I was nine, and shortly after that decision, I lost my father to cancer. I truly believe that God has a sovereign plan for our lives and even through that hurt and pain I was able to learn and grow and trust God wholly and fully. I have been a member at Faith Promise Church since February, 2015 and I have a strong desire to see God\\u2019s love spread throughout this wonderful city.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Music is my passion. I believe that God created art and he gives us creativity and so naturally I appreciate art and creativity myself. Muse is my favorite band and has been since I was a freshman in high school. Fun Fact: I saw them live for my sixteenth birthday and cried. Real tears. As much as I love music though, I grew up first loving sports. Tennis and basketball are my two favorite sports. Novak Djokovic is my favorite tennis player and my favorite basketball team is THE UNIVERSITY OF KENTUCKY. If you\\u2019ll notice, my top player and team are both the best. Before you call me a bandwagon fan, I had pictures of Djokovic on my Myspace page and both sides of my family are die-hard Kentucky fans. Go cats!<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"LanceA@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"lance.asher.9\",\"16\":\"Lance\",\"25\":\"lancejasher\",\"19\":\"Worship Associate - Next Generation Band\",\"17\":\"Asher\",\"26\":[\"27\"],\"27\":[\"451\"],\"24\":\"LanceJAsher\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:47', '2017-09-01 18:40:47', '6682b6c2-d189-4057-b1eb-95b9017e354d'),
 ('429', '389', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Hannah Little\",\"slug\":\"hannah-little\",\"postDate\":1478235600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"HannahL@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Hannah\",\"19\":\"Student Associate\",\"17\":\"Little\",\"26\":[\"25\"],\"27\":[\"426\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:53', '2017-09-01 18:40:53', '175b90bf-4bce-4779-99e1-90e3af7a49c7'),
 ('430', '391', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Justin Petrowski\",\"slug\":\"justin-petrowski\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I\'ve been a follower of Christ since 1987 and can say with confidence that it\'s the best decision I\'ve ever made. I have been a member of Faith Promise Church since its inception in 1995. I have always enjoyed serving here - so when the opportunity arose to serve here full-time I took it! I have been on staff at Faith Promise since 2001 as an intern in the Worship Ministry and have served on full-time staff since 2003. Since then I\'ve had the unique privilege of ministering to thousands of my brothers and sisters each week through my gift of music. I attended Oak Ridge High School in Oak Ridge, TN and graduated there in 1999. I attended the University of Tennessee after that and graduated in 2003 with an honors degree in mathematics. I have been married to my beautiful wife Kara since October 2006.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I love to read, watch and play sports, and make music. I enjoy spending time with my wife and with friends. As far as music goes, I love it all...you\'ll find me listening to anything from Coltrane to Coldplay, Sigur Ros to Sergei Rachmaninoff, U2 to the David Crowder Band and Hillsong. I\'m always into something different. I love to read as well and I love exploring the Bible through fresh sets of eyes. Some of my favorite books include Velvet Elvis by Rob Bell, Blue Like Jazz by Donald Miller, and A Generous Orthodoxy by Brian McLaren. Check them out! I\'m also a HUGE fan of the Green Bay Packers, the Boston Red Sox, NASCAR, and University of Tennessee athletics. Go VOLS!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>God bless you!\\nHebrews 12:1-3<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"JustinP@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"justin.lee.petrowski\",\"16\":\"Justin\",\"25\":\"petrowski7\",\"19\":\"Band Director\",\"17\":\"Petrowski\",\"26\":[\"27\"],\"22\":\"1502\",\"27\":[\"444\"],\"24\":\"petrowski7\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:58', '2017-09-01 18:40:58', '402a04d1-f828-4b8f-b51e-5512acf74e55');
