 ('431', '393', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jennifer Rose\",\"slug\":\"jennifer-rose\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":1476853200,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"21\":\"JenniferR@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"jennifer.rose.94\",\"16\":\"Jennifer\",\"19\":\"Assistant to the Pastor of Leadership Development & Stewardship\",\"17\":\"Rose\",\"22\":\"1100\",\"24\":\"jrose1001\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:40:58', '2017-09-01 18:40:58', '94734deb-bd74-48d4-a27e-b7a57dbb5cc0'),
 ('432', '395', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Martha Williams\",\"slug\":\"martha-williams\",\"postDate\":1477285200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Hi.  My name is Martha Williams.  I moved to the Knoxville area in 2013 from Washington State to be with my daughter and her family.  After losing several family members to cancer, including my parents and husband, it was time for a change and to be close to my 4 grandchildren (2 girls and 2 boys). Moving to Knoxville meant that I left behind my son and his then new bride.  Now, I\'m missing their first daughter and a second daughter due January, 2017.  It just means I get to go back and visit them as often as I can!<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>When I would visit Knoxville, I would always attend Faith Promise with my family.  There was no question where I was going to attend church once I moved here.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>After my husband\'s death in 2005, I took over the operation of his business, a produce brokerage. Prior to that I had been a CPA, working in private accounting, industry and government.  In the beginning of 2016 I entered into semi-retirement. I had been praying and asking God what this next season would look like.  I felt God telling me to trust Him, that he had something good planned.  I had been volunteering in the Finance office when I was asked if I would take a temporary position, filling in for someone on medical leave.  That led to my position as HR Administrator.  I am so honored to work with such a great team of people, furthering the vision and mission of saving souls in East Tennessee.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I love to travel, whether to visit family or exploring and trying new things.  My favorite places to go are Moloka\\u2019i, Hawaii and the San Juan Islands in Washington State.  Anything that involves being on or in the water \\u2013 swimming, boating or scuba diving.  In 2010 I got my open water scuba diving certification and my advanced open water in 2014.  Now I try to mix my travels with scuba diving.  When home I enjoy working in the yard, quilting, knitting and spending time with family and my dear sisters in my small groups.  I look forward to what God has planned for this next stage in life.  He is faithful and \\\"I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me\\u201d Phil 4:13.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"marthaw@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Martha\",\"19\":\"HR Administrator\",\"17\":\"Williams\",\"26\":[\"28\",\"28\"],\"27\":[\"460\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:41:03', '2017-09-01 18:41:03', 'e3cc0dcb-84b3-46b5-a78d-1faf756bbfb1'),
 ('433', '397', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kelly Carringer\",\"slug\":\"kelly-carringer\",\"postDate\":1476853200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was born and raised in Knoxville, TN. I\\u2019m the youngest of 7 and have a twin. Growing up in a big family is a huge blessing! I\\u2019ve learned so much from watching other people, and God has taught me so much from my family.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I\\u2019ve been attending Faith Promise since August 2010, and I\\u2019m truly blown away by the impact it\\u2019s had on my life. I\\u2019m thrilled to join my husband and the rest of the team on staff! Small groups have grown my walk tremendously and fostered lifelong friendships. I can\\u2019t wait to help other people find the perfect group for their season of life.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Outside of work, I love to travel! You might also find me baking, watching movies, and loving anything Disney.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"6\"],\"21\":\"kellyc@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Kelly\",\"19\":\"Pellissippi Groups Administrative Assistant\",\"17\":\"Carringer\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"27\":[\"446\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:41:07', '2017-09-01 18:41:07', 'c12ec0bd-7919-4274-a4cd-52c55b90c85f'),
 ('434', '399', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Miles Creasman\",\"slug\":\"miles-creasman\",\"postDate\":1439933611,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>Miles Creasman has been on staff as the Blount Campus Groups Director since June 2010 and also took on the role of Pastor of Next Steps in the middle of 2011. Originally from Riceville, TN, Miles is a graduate of Carson-Newman College and Southern Baptist Theological Seminary in Louisville, KY. He has been in ministry for 15 years and has served on church staffs as Recreation Minister, Middle &amp; High School Pastor, and Singles Pastor.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Miles has a passion to help people grow in their relationship with the Lord, and he believes that the context of community found in groups is the best place for that to happen.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Miles has been married to Katy for 13 years, and they have 3 children - Jess (9), Will (7), and Leah (3).<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Miles\' favorite hobby is playing with his kids. He loves playing Frisbee golf &amp; fantasy sports. Miles and Katy are both very big UT Vols fans and love to go to games whenever they can.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"9\"],\"21\":\"MilesC@faithpromise.org\",\"23\":\"miles.creasman\",\"16\":\"Miles\",\"25\":\"bigorange999\",\"19\":\"Blount Campus Pastor of Groups & Missions\",\"17\":\"Creasman\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"22\":\"1005\",\"27\":[\"467\"],\"24\":\"Bigorange99\"}}', '2017-09-01 18:41:13', '2017-09-01 18:41:13', 'bba234ec-299f-47fb-9ea1-291e3d96984d'),
 ('435', '536', '3', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Robbie Freeman\",\"slug\":\"robbie-freeman\",\"postDate\":1473656400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"20\":\"<p>I was born in Virginia Beach, but my dad\\u2019s career in the Navy took us all over the world. We lived in California, Washington, Mississippi, Ohio, Virginia, Washington D.C., and lived in Scotland for five years.  I began my walk with Christ when I was thirteen-years-old, but joining Faith Promise in 2012 revitalized my faith. My wife Cher and I have been married for many moons and have two rambunctious boys - Ryder and Eli. Cher also has two additional furry children. They are her Yorkie, Aristotle, and Meiko. We love spending time outdoors hiking and stand-up paddle boarding, and playing soccer.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>I earned my Bachelor\\u2019s Degree from the University of Memphis in Communications, and I am currently working on a Master\\u2019s Degree in Christian Apologetics at Liberty University. I was a Small Group leader, and coach at the Pellissippi campus for several years and joined the Anderson County campus in August of 2016 as Small Groups Pastor.  I spent fifteen years in restaurant management and currently am a General Manager for Gordon Food Services.<\\/p>\\n\\n<p>My ministry goal is to glorify God through transformed lives, and I think that small groups are the perfect ministry for that purpose. The Bible passage that I focus my life on is Colossians 1:28-29.<\\/p>\",\"14\":[\"13\"],\"21\":\"robbief@faithpromise.org\",\"16\":\"Robbie\",\"19\":\"Anderson Campus Pastor of Groups & Missions\",\"17\":\"Freeman\",\"26\":[\"26\"],\"27\":[\"474\"]}}', '2017-09-01 18:41:18', '2017-09-01 18:41:18', '713a970d-a912-4324-a156-37dcc124241c'),
