 ('188', 'field', '20', 'en_us', ' my husband david and i started attending faith promise in october 2004 i came on staff in early 2007 and i am so humbled that god allows me to be even the tiniest part of what he is doing here at fpc in 1998 david our two sons sean and ryan and i set out from south florida to our promised land with hurricane georges traveling along beside us our little family of four that moved to east tennessee has grown in the ten years that we have been here we have added to our family a lovely daughter in law christy and two precious grandchildren colin and audrey we are blessed more than we could hope or imagine i love to spend time with my family especially the grandkids truly a gift from god i have been classified by my husband as not just a book lover but a book collector i love to read especially anything that draws me closer to the lord i also enjoy sudoku hiking camping geocaching target practice and riding the motorcycle with my hubby my favorite food it might be easier to list what i don t like sushi rhubarb and liver everything else is my favorite especially anything italian mexican asian mediterranean cajun or american unusual well i would have to say yes i am but that s not what you meant i want the truth no matter how painful just give it to me straight no fluff and please please do not beat around the bush oh yeah and check out the left pinky toe when i m wearing flip flops or barefoot facebook at nancy bachor '),
