 ('243', 'field', '20', 'en_us', ' paul was born in new york but moved shortly thereafter and was raised in knoxville tennessee paul grew up as a middle child and accredits middle child syndrome as the cause of his outgoing personality and constant humor paul began his call to ministry during high school working many summers at a christian camp in asheville north carolina he later attended boyce college at southern seminary in louisville kentucky studying youth ministry and biblical studies and then returned to tennessee in 2007 to pursue a degree in video production at pellissippi state a year and a half later he met his beautiful wife kelly and the 2 were married in may 2010 if he could be any type of animal paul would probably be an otter firstly because they get to experience land and water and secondly because they always seem to be the animals having the most fun every time he goes to the zoo paul loves anything to do with travel and visiting new places which probably stems from his dad being a pilot and has been to all 50 states and over a dozen countries he also enjoys movies music boats the mountains and being around people paul made a living freelance shooting and editing video for commercials concerts weddings and sports before joining the faith promise staff in early 2010 as the student ministries program director paul s passion for youth ministry and love of technology drive him to serve god wholeheartedly in his position using the gifts that god has given him '),
