 ('251', 'field', '20', 'en_us', ' i grew up in a home where we put the lord first period because my parents were such strong christian models for me i became a christ follower at a young age and never looked back i grew up in knoxville attended bearden high school and then went on to ut to study journalism and electronic media i started attending faith promise in college 2004 and immediately felt drawn to the heart and mission of my new church family making it hard to go to hell from east tennessee after graduating college i moved to the tri cities to take my first tv reporting job at wjhl it s there that i met and fell head over heels in love with my husband after my contract was up i came back in knoxville shawn and i married in 2009 and i was thrilled to bring my husband to faith promise the church where i felt at home in 2010 the lord began to work on my heart at that point i had been in tv news for six years locally i worked for wate and wvlt and that was all i knew of the career world it had been my dream but i began to feel uneasy i knew it wasn t my heart s desire anymore that was truly scary for such a control freak like me it was scary until i heard four words from executive pastor josh whitehead you want a job yes if there s anything else i d rather be doing it s serving my god in ministry and family ministry that s perfect i know first hand the difference a strong foundation makes and i d love to dedicate myself to helping others live that abundant life out at home so that s how i went from working in tv to working for jesus let me encourage you to never ignore that still small voice he may be calling you to the greatest adventure of your life if you want to join me without making a huge life change come serve in fpkids what a joy it is '),
