 ('256', 'field', '20', 'en_us', ' hey my name is justine i started coming to faith promise in 2006 and attended with my family until i moved to birmingham alabama for an internship program with a church there after returning to knoxville in 2011 my love for faith promise grew and i knew that it was a place i wanted to be a part of in the fall of 2011 god answered my prayers and blessed me with the opportunity to serve on staff a few months later he opened the door for me to become the apprentice coordinator of student ministries the title is just a fancy name for helping people put action to the calling that they feel god has given them i know that the lord has incredible plans for this church and i fully believe that he is going to use faith promise to make it hard to go to hell not only from east tennessee but also from the nations as well as working with our volunteers in fpstudents and helping people get involved here at fpc i also have a passion for working with young girls to help them realize who they are in christ i believe that you don t have to be in your twenties or later to find god and truly experience his love because of this passion i am currently working on my bachelor s in psychology at the university of tennessee i m not sure how god is going to use me exactly all i know is that i am ready and willing to go wherever he leads '),
