 ('395', 'field', '20', 'en_us', ' hi my name is martha williams i moved to the knoxville area in 2013 from washington state to be with my daughter and her family after losing several family members to cancer including my parents and husband it was time for a change and to be close to my 4 grandchildren 2 girls and 2 boys moving to knoxville meant that i left behind my son and his then new bride now i m missing their first daughter and a second daughter due january 2017 it just means i get to go back and visit them as often as i can when i would visit knoxville i would always attend faith promise with my family there was no question where i was going to attend church once i moved here after my husband s death in 2005 i took over the operation of his business a produce brokerage prior to that i had been a cpa working in private accounting industry and government in the beginning of 2016 i entered into semi retirement i had been praying and asking god what this next season would look like i felt god telling me to trust him that he had something good planned i had been volunteering in the finance office when i was asked if i would take a temporary position filling in for someone on medical leave that led to my position as hr administrator i am so honored to work with such a great team of people furthering the vision and mission of saving souls in east tennessee i love to travel whether to visit family or exploring and trying new things my favorite places to go are moloka i hawaii and the san juan islands in washington state anything that involves being on or in the water swimming boating or scuba diving in 2010 i got my open water scuba diving certification and my advanced open water in 2014 now i try to mix my travels with scuba diving when home i enjoy working in the yard quilting knitting and spending time with family and my dear sisters in my small groups i look forward to what god has planned for this next stage in life he is faithful and i can do all things through christ who strengthens me phil 4 13 '),
